title: six can soup
directions: Cook ground chuck about 10 minutes and drain.
Mix all ingredients in a 5-quart cooking pot.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer for about 1 hour.
Add some water and salt.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook pork until light brown.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Season to taste.
For New England style, omit last 4 ingredients and after cooking, add 2 tablespoons butter and 2 cups of milk.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Add vinegar, sugar and water.
Let cool slightly, then pour over mixed vegetables and let cool a good 30 minutes before putting in freezer.

title: desert rasmalai
directions: Set aside 2 to 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Crush the cardamom to powder.
Mix cheese, sugar, milk powder and one crushed cardamom thoroughly.
Spread the mixture in a 13 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan; bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove; sprinkle almonds on top and let cool for an hour.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed, adding oil slowly.
Stir in seeds.

title: three-citrus chicken salad
directions: Divide greens among 6 plates. Arrange chicken, grapefruit sections, orange sections and red onion slices on top of greens.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Add Hershey Kiss to each cookie and bake additional 2 minutes.

title: chicken stuffing bake
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to box directions.
Mix soup and milk.
Arrange stuffing across middle of baking dish.
Spoon thin layer of soup mixture on each side.
Layer chicken breasts. Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour remaining soup over chicken.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook until slightly crisp.
Do not overcook. Cool.
Put salt, pepper, sugar, tomato soup, oil and vinegar in mixer and beat 5 minutes.
Pour over carrots.
Add onion and green pepper sliced paper thin.
Marinate overnight.
Store in glass jar in refrigerator.
Keeps 2 weeks or more.
When carrots are gone, use the liquid on salads.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together, then add cake mix.
Mix together and pat in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Mix all together the remaining ingredients and pour on cake mix.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 55 minutes at 300°.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until crumbly; reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), building up 1/2-inch edges.
Spread pie filling over cake mixture to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Mix nuts and reserved mixture; sprinkle over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm, if desired, with any whipped topping or ice cream.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with ham.
Add shredded Cheddar or Swiss cheese.
Mix eggs and milk together and pour over the top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let soak overnight. Bake in 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies
directions: Mix and put over first mixture.
Bake at least 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rambo refrigerator rolls
directions: In large bowl, pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt. Mix well; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat in eggs. Add to cooled butter mixture.
Mix in the flour; stir well. Cover loosely; let rise overnight in refrigerator.
Shape at least 2 hours before baking in a 400° oven.
Recipe makes about 60 rolls.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar gradually. Add eggs one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk. Bake in stem cake pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: hillbilly stew
directions: Brown sirloin tips in oil 5 minutes.
Cut potatoes into chunks.
In a large pot, combine steak, tomatoes, okra, potatoes, succotash, onions, garlic powder, garlic salt, sugar, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crumbs or wheat germ. Grease a 1-quart casserole dish or individual custard cups and sprinkle bottom with some crumbs or wheat germ. Pour in pudding mix and sprinkle more crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Mix with chopped fresh fruits such as apples, pears, peaches, bananas or strawberries. Add marshmallows and nuts, if desired.
Mix in Cool Whip.

title: spinach braid
directions: Mix spinach (dry), cheeses and garlic.
Roll out each package of crescent rolls to make two rectangles; seal seams.
Place 1/2 mix on each rectangle; place 1-inch pieces of Provolone on top. Cut 1-inch strips, diagonally and cross over filling and seal. Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate chip cheese bars
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch baking pan with half the cookie dough slices. Beat cream cheese, eggs and sugar until smooth.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Spread over cookie dough layer.
Top with remaining slices of dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: congealed cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatins and water until completely dissolved. Add cranberry sauce and stir until melted.

Add drained pineapple, nuts and celery. Pour into 2-quart mold or into individual molds and place in refrigerator until set. Unmold on bed of lettuce leaves and drizzle with the following dressing, if desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Tear cauliflower and broccoli heads apart.
Mix with olives and sliced carrots.
Cover with dressing and sprinkle on cheese.
Mix well.

title: shrimp cocktail dip
directions: With hands, pat softened cream cheese onto an 11 or 12-inch pie plate.
Pour sauce over cream cheese and spread evenly. Drain seafood.
Drop shrimp evenly on sauce; do not mix.
Serve with large Fritos which act as a scoop.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Spread pretzels on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix melted oleo or butter with 2 tablespoons sugar and pour over pretzels and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Whip together the cream cheese and Cool Whip and 3/4 cup sugar.
Spread over cooled pretzels.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin with 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and the sliced strawberries.
When cool and starting to gel, pour over the cream cheese layer and let set until firm.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break up crabmeat; stir in bread crumbs and remaining ingredients except butter.
Divide crab into 8 portions and place in hot butter in skillet.
Flatten into patties and brown well on both sides.
Serve plain or with tartar sauce and lemon wedges.

title: strawberry surprise salad
directions: Using 2 bowls, mix all ingredients together.
Example: One package jello, 1 cup hot water, 1/2 cup cold water, 1 package strawberries and 1/2 can of pineapple.
Do not drain strawberries and pineapple, use the juice.
After you have combined the ingredients, put half the mixture in a large square pan. Refrigerate until firm; leave other half of mixture set out.
When refrigerated jello mixture has gotten firm, spread sour cream on top, then pour the rest of the liquid mixture on top.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Set aside.
Mix oil, eggs and strawberries.
Fold together. Add nuts.
Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Boil spaghetti according to directions on package.
Drain. Mix favorite brand of spaghetti sauce into spaghetti.
Sprinkle a layer of Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until melted. Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: pecan pie #2
directions: Combine butter, sugar and corn syrup. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Add eggs after they have been beaten and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and top with pecan halves. Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: spanish rump roast
directions: Brown meat in 1/4 cup dressing in a large Dutch oven or large heavy pot that will hold meat and vegetables.
Add remaining dressing and 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
After 2 hours, add onions, potatoes,
carrots and olives.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes more or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove meat and vegetables to serving platter.
In a mixing bowl, gradually add 1/4 cup water to flour, stirring until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture to hot liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve sauce over meat and vegetables.

title: holiday truffles
directions: Melt chocolate chips in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in orange liqueur and frosting; blend well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm. Place coconut in pie pan.
Scoop mixture into 1-inch balls; drop onto coconut.
(Mixture will be sticky.)
Roll to coat.
Place in foil candy cups, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen candies.

title: confectioners sugar pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat the butter until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Beat in vanilla.
Gradually and gently stir in flour, blending just until incorporated. (Do not overmix.) Turn into a well buttered and lightly floured 3-quart fluted or plain pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until pick inserted comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes in pan. Turn on rack to cool. Sprinkle cooled cake with confectioners sugar. Freezes well.

title: sandy's chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° to serving temperature.

title: pizza casserole(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 30 to 40 minutes.

title: superman's favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Add flour, soda, salt and oatmeal.
Carefully mix in Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in salt water until tender.
Cook onion and carrots in butter for about 10 minutes in a large skillet.
Stir in sour cream, 2 cups stuffing mix, zucchini and soup.
Mix and pour into an uncovered buttered dish and put remaining butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato-bean soup(low-fat soup - heart healthy)
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir celery, carrots and garlic in hot margarine over medium heat for 4 minutes or until tender.
Stir in broth, potatoes and dill.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender. With the back of a spoon, lightly mash about half of the potatoes in the broth.
Add the drained beans.
In a small bowl, stir together sour cream or yogurt, flour and salt, if desired.
Stir this into the potato mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbling.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grate
everything together in a bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and if possible let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: rum balls
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate pieces over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Fold in vanilla wafers and nuts.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peach pickle
directions: Put peaches in glass container.
Drain syrup from peaches; add vinegar, spices and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour over peaches.
Let stand for 24 hours before using.

title: cream sherry cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth according to directions on box.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mayonnaise, in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Chop 3 heads of lettuce and 2 heads of Romaine lettuce. Place in separate bowl.
Do not mix with ingredients until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, mix all ingredients, including mayonnaise, and mix well.
Serve.
Serves 10 or more.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in tightly closed container and refrigerate several hours; overnight is best.
Drain before serving.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa together. Spread into a 13 x 9 baking dish and sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top. Bake at 350° until hot or cheese is bubbling.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, taco seasoning and green chilies until well blended. Pour into serving dish and garnish with favorite toppings. Serve with Tostitos or Fritos.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with gravy
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as per package directions. Cut breasts in halves and pound flat. Roll the chicken breast around a mound of stuffing and place in a greased baking dish.
Mix soup with the milk. Add mushrooms and pour over chicken. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook and remove bone from chicken (reserve liquid).
Cut chicken into desired pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup and reserved liquid.
Thicken this slightly; salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken pieces.
Make Jiffy mix dumplings.
Drop dumpling mixture by tablespoons into bubbling chicken.
Cook until done.

title: golden punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Mix well with next 3 ingredients.
Add sherbet at last minute.

title: pepper pot
directions: Wash and clean all meats; cut into bite size pieces.
Place meats in large mixing bowl.
Add chopped garlic clove, salt, pepper, thyme, finely chopped spring/green onions and whole hot pepper.
Do not chop hot pepper.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Mix and let stand for 1 hour (the longer you allow meat to marinate, the more seasoned the meat will taste).

title: marjorie whitfield's quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Stir in yeast mixture and add melted butter.
Knead lightly in dough pan with just enough flour to make the dough soft so it can be handled.
Let stand 15 minutes in covered bowl in a warm place.
Turn out on floured board and knead lightly.
Boil to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out and let rise 1 hour.
Bake in a 400° oven about 10 minutes.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Whip first 4 ingredients with a fork until like whipped cream. Sift in flour; stir quickly with "round bowl" strokes.

title: orange date cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine 3 3/4 cups of flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; beat well after each addition.
Dredge dates and pecans in remaining 1/4 cup of flour. Stir into batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle top with orange rind.
Bake at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.
Use a wooden pick to punch holes in top of cake, then while cake is still warm, pour orange glaze over top.
Let cake cool before removing from pan.

title: low carb mousse
directions: Empty into bowl.
Substitute cream for milk.
Mix.
Chill. Any flavor is good.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
Shake well to blend.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into oblong rectangles. Place them crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; press over bottom and 1 inch up sides to form crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
In small bowl, combine sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper; blend until smooth.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Top with mushrooms, tomatoes, broccoli, green pepper and onions.
Cut into appetizer-size pieces.
Makes 60 appetizers.

title: stuffing casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine water and margarine; stir until margarine is melted.
Add stuffing mix.
Spoon half of stuffing into an 8-inch baking dish.
Save remaining stuffing.
Cook meat; drain fat.
Add beans, tomatoes and spices.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon over stuffing in dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, saving half of cheese.
Top with remaining stuffing and cheese. Bake 30 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream, if desired.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Chill until almost set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Line bottom of dish with half of the wafer crumbs.
Pour in Jell-O mixture.
Top with remaining wafer crumbs.

title: marinated slaw pressley
directions: Shred cabbage.
Grate onion and pepper on top.
Top with sugar.
Bring to a boil the salad oil, vinegar, dry mustard, celery seed and salt.
Pour mixture over cabbage.
Let sit overnight.
Serves 6.

title: date filled oatmeal bars
directions: Cook dates in water until tender; add sugar and lemon juice. Cool.
Mix and sift dry ingredients; add oatmeal.
Cut in shortening.
Press 1/2 of mixture on bottom of 9-inch square pan. Cover with date mixture.
Sprinkle remaining dry
mixture on top. Press lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: bird's nest pie
directions: Divide apples evenly between two greased 9-inch pie plates. Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cream of tartar, sour milk and egg.
Mix well.
Divide butter and pour over apples. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pies are lightly browned and tests done.
Flip onto serving plates (so apples are on top). Sprinkle topping on apples. Serve warm. Makes 12 servings.

title: tropical trifle
directions: Cut cake into cubes.
Prepare pudding and pie filling as directed on package.
Fold orange peel and half of whipped topping into pudding.

title: icing
directions: Mix and boil 2 minutes, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Then add 1 cup coconut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together in butter until broccoli is tender.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Stir in blueberries and orange peel.
In another bowl, beat the eggs; add milk and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: coconut pecan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: orange salad
directions: Blend jello into Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients and blend. Refrigerate for about 30 minutes and serve.
That's it!

title: white buttermilk cake
directions: Beat sugar, oleo and egg whites until fluffy.
To buttermilk, add soda and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Alternate into egg whites the buttermilk mixture and flour mixture, ending with flour mixture.
Pour into lined 9-inch round pan or greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until it springs back.
Cool and frost.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: In medium-sized bowl, combine butter, sugar and salt.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each addition. Stir in vanilla, flour, cream and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg, vinegar and water together.
Add to mixture; mold and chill 15 minutes.
May store 3 days in refrigerator or freeze.
I like to divide mixture into single crust size portions and freeze in Ziploc bags for future use.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Stir constantly.
Chill and serve hot or cold.
This goes well with braised beef brisket.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 teaspoons water.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Spoon in greased muffin pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: club fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit, nuts, whipped cream, marshmallows and cooled cooked mixture.
Pour into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add flour and milk. Add cheese to hot mixture.
Let cool slightly and add sour cream and green beans.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Mix cornflakes in
2 tablespoons margarine, melted and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 325° until bubbly and browned.

title: red beans and rice
directions: *Omit sausage and oil for a nearly fat-free main dish.

title: lachssteaks mit zitronenschaum(salmon steaks with foaming lemon sauce)
directions: Rinse the fish under cold running water if necessary, pat dry and season with salt.
Heat the oil in a pan and add the butter or margarine.
When the butter or margarine has melted, fry the salmon steaks on each side.
Place in a warmed dish and keep warm.

title: mexican fiesta dip
directions: Melt the cream cheese in Corning Ware dish.
Pour the salsa over the cream cheese. Sprinkle grated Cheddar on top.
Melt in oven. Pour over tortilla chips.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears in food chopper; drain.
Grind peppers and onions. Combine all ingredients except vinegar.
Cover with vinegar. Cook slowly for 1 hour.
Yields 6 pints.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix ingredients well except for cucumbers.
Pour mixture over cucumbers and soak for 3 days.
On the third day, pack pickles firmly into freezer containers and pour liquid over the pickles. Seal and freeze.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on package.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated oven of 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Blend pudding mix with milk; beat in cream cheese (room temperature), then fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake.
Sprinkle drained pineapple over pudding, then cherries, nuts and coconut. Refrigerate until ready to cut.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: cloud 9 ambrosia salad
directions: Lightly combine all ingredients until well mixed. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease (not oil) and lightly flour bottom of loaf pan.
In large bowl blend all ingredients except eggs and nuts at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Add eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts. Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire racks.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Slowly pour in oil, beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake in Greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
To remove cake from pan, go around tube real good with knife before taking up.

title: mexican hominy skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef.
Drain off fat.
Stir in hominy, green pepper, water, chili seasoning and soup.
Cook and stir until heated through.
Sprinkle cheese over meat, cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter until creamy.
Add sugar; beat well.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Shape in balls.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Brown cubed steak. In crock-pot, put your 3 cans soup and the water. Place browned steak in soup mixture. Cook on high about 3 to 4 hours. Should be ready to eat.

title: steamed cauliflower and sauce
directions: Steam cauliflower.
Mix mayonnaise with mustard.
Spread over hot vegetables; cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and put under broiler until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Use enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour gradually until dough is stiff.
Roll out and cut into shape or roll like biscuit and pat onto the cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Place rice, mushroom soup and onion soup in dish; mix together.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: minty chocolate cake
directions: Start with Duncan Hines dark Dutch fudge cake mix.
Add peppermint extract to the batter while mixing.
Bake and cool as directed, then sprinkle crushed peppermint candy on top of frosted cake.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk together.
Bring to a hard boil. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove and add peanut butter. Beat until it starts to thicken and spread on cake.

title: chicken breast diane
directions: Place chicken breast halves between sheets of waxed paper; pound slightly with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat 3 minutes on each side and transfer to warm serving platter.

title: bran rolls
directions: Mix boiling water, Crisco, sugar, bran and salt; let cool. Add eggs and yeast, dissolved in water.
Add flour and mix well. Let rise 2 hours or store in refrigerator.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: patable pie crust
directions: Spray 9-inch glass pie plate with Pam; set aside.
Combine flour, oil and salt in medium bowl.
Add water and stir to form a ball.
Place dough in pan and use fingers to pat into a uniform thickness on bottom and sides.
Flute edges.
Use for unbaked or to bake, bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or lightly brown.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and herbs.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes. Combine 1/2 of Parmesan, cottage (or Ricotta) cheese and egg until well blended; set aside.

title: queen of hearts tarts
directions: You will also need 2 non-stick muffin tins, pot holder and teaspoon.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Boil first 2 ingredients for 10 minutes at rapid boil, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour in pan and let it cool.
Cut into squares.

title: ginny baker's fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift flour with salt and soda and combine with mixture.
Add vanilla.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Start in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, honey and cinnamon.
With fingers, mix in 4 tablespoons butter until crumbs form.
Arrange 4 cups cored, peeled and sliced tart apples in a 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamed potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into eighths; cut onion into eighths.
Coarsely chop the green onions and add them along with the garlic to the butter in a heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Add onion to butter and saute for 1 minute.
Add the potatoes and pour in the broth.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Puree soup in food processor or blender in batches that suit the size of appliance. Add cream, milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Chill if served cold, reheat to serving temperature if serving hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crunchy cheese potatoes(yields 8 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, combine sour cream or milk, chives, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and mix thoroughly.
Spread in a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Combine cheese and corn flakes; sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with additional chives if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni with salt for 8 to 10 minutes and drain. In large bowl, mix macaroni, cheese and eggs together. Salt and pepper to taste. Add enough milk to cover macaroni well. Pour into large buttered casserole dish. Cook at 375° for 1 hour.

title: bailey's irish cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the chocolate chips, until blended well. Add in the chocolate chips. Butter a Bundt pan (very well) and pour the batter into it evenly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange-cranberry torte
directions: Start heating oven to 350°.
Sift together into a bowl the flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Stir in the nuts, dates, cranberries and the orange rind.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and salad oil.
Add to flour-fruit mixture.
Stir until blended.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let come to a boil.
Cook until forms a soft ball in 1/4 cup cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick and smooth.
Pour into buttered plate or small pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: crispy croutons
directions: In small glass bowl, heat butter at High 1 minute or until melted.
Brush butter onto bread (one side only).
Cut bread into small cubes.
In oblong baking dish, arrange bread; drizzle with remaining butter.
Heat at High 5 to 6 minutes or until bread is crispy; stir twice.
To complete, let stand 10 minutes, stored and covered, until ready to serve.
Yields 3 cups.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend together sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture; mix until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in 325° oven.

title: marjorie's "big" banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; set aside.
Beat egg yolks (whites are for meringue).
Add 4 cups milk.
Add this to sugar mixture and stir.
Add remaining milk and vanilla.
Cook in double boiler until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and cool.
Layer bananas and vanilla wafers.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 1 cup sugar and beat again.
Pour cooled pudding over layered bananas and top with beaten egg whites.
Put in 400° oven until lightly brown.

title: chocolate chip raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add oatmeal.
Let stand a few minutes.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs with wire whisk.
Add flour and sugar.
Add milk, cheese, butter.
Add corn and mix very well.
Lightly butter baking dish.
Pour mixture in.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: pineapple-cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add pineapple and nuts. Chill bread overnight.
Coat bread with salad dressing before spreading with filling.
Trim edges; cut in half before serving (optional).

title: beef zucchini casserole
directions: In a large skillet, saute zucchini and onion in margarine until onion is tender.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Set aside.

title: crispy cheese
directions: Grate one or two ounces of cheese into microwave-safe dish, preferably fairly flat.
Microwave on High until no longer runny and is full of little holes.
Drain liquid, put cheese on paper towels to cool, then break into pieces and serve.

title: fresh sourdough biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; add starter. Mix to make firm dough. Add water, if needed. Cover and let rest 5 minutes. Keep adding equal amounts of water and all-purpose flour to keep starter going. After adding, let sit overnight before using.

title: cowboy enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add Velveeta cheese and cook until melted.
In a saucepan, heat soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Roll beef and cheese mixture in flour tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup mixture over tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered tortilla pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic in margarine.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper.
In round 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Pour water at edge of casserole onto bottom.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and let stand 5 minutes before cutting wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls; press with fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Put in diced chicken breasts.
Add soup and broth.
Cover with unprepared stuffing mix and dot with oleo or butter.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes for an excellent meal.

title: hawaiian-style parsnips
directions: Peel and slice parsnips.
Cook in small amount of salted water until tender (15 to 20 minutes); drain well.
In large saucepan blend brown sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in undrained pineapple, orange peel and orange juice.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add butter; stir until melted.
Add parsnips to sauce.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool about 1 hour.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream; spread on top of frozen cookie mixture.
Re-freeze.
Bring to a boil the sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla, chocolate and 6 tablespoons margarine.
Boil 1 minute, then cool.
Pour over ice cream and re-freeze.
Mix Cool Whip with toasted pecans.
Spread on top. Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, cinnamon and vanilla; stir.
Add apples, raisins and nuts. Fold these in until mixed well.
This makes a thick stiff batter and will need to be spooned evenly into a well-greased and floured pan.
I use a Bundt or angel food pan.
It fits nicely into a medium loaf pan also.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) until lightly brown.

title: thirty-six lady prune cake
directions: In
electric
blender, combine prunes and water.
Blend until smooth, scraping sides of container as needed.
Combine prunes and
remaining
ingredients
except glaze and garnish. Mix	until thoroughly blended.
Turn into greased and floured 12-cup tube pan.
Bake	in
a
oven 65 to 70 minutes or until cake
is springy to the touch and toothpick inserted in center comes
out clean.
Cool
cake in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto
serving plate and pierce all over with fork.
Slowly pour
glaze
over cake.
Garnish
as	desired
with remaining prunes and nuts.

title: blueberry whip
directions: Melt butter; add graham cracker crumbs and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix together and pat firmly on bottom of an 11 x 11-inch dish.
Mix the Dream Whip and milk; beat on high speed until it makes stiff peaks.
Then add softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Spread the blueberry pie filling on top.
Chill 3 hours or overnight before serving.

title: skillet baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and add onions.
Saute 5 minutes. Add pork and beans, brown sugar and catsup.
Simmer 20 minutes and serve.

title: hamburger cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slightly grease 2 (8-inch) or 9-inch pie pans.
Cook beef and onion until brown; drain grease.
Add salt and pepper; stir.
Spread mixture into pie pans.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth; pour over meat and cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes, until golden brown, or until tester comes out clean.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Enjoy!

title: rhubarb or peach crunch
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, cinnamon and butter until crumbly.
Press half of mixture into a greased 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb or peaches.
Combine remaining ingredients and cook until thick and clear.
Pour over fruit.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix baking soda and vinegar.
Sit a minute.
Add cocoa and red food coloring, then set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix.
Add flour and salt.
Mix.
Add red mixture.
Mix.
Pour into greased floured pans.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Make Jell-O.
Add drained pineapple (save juice).
Put in a large bowl.
Add bananas and marshmallows.
Let Jell-O set.

title: artichoke spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Fold into glass pie dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve warm with crackers.

title: apple cobbler(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray pie plate with vegetable pan coating.
Combine apples, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Combine cornstarch, apple pie spice, salt and sugar substitute.
Mix thoroughly.
Add to apples and stir lightly with fork to coat apples.
Spread evenly in pie plate. Mix together flour and salt. Cut in margarine with fork until crumbly; scatter over apples. Bake 35 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Beat in blender.
Water first, then add dry ingredients and margarine, beating until well blended.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Equals 1 can of sweetened condensed milk.

title: coconut-orange chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Combine eggs and next three ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Add coconut.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until filling is set.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Boil peeled and quartered eggplant in salt water until tender.
Soak 2 slices of bread in milk.
Mash eggplant with bread.
Add eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix cheese with this and put in greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Add water to pastry mix, a small amount at a time.
Mix quickly and evenly with a fork until the dough just forms a ball. Roll to 1/8 inch thickness.
Sprinkle half the cheese and salt on half the pastry.
Repeat folding process and roll to 1/4 inch. Cut into strips.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Stir in flour.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: double-crust chicken pie
directions: Fix bottom pie crust in pie pan; do not bake.
Combine rest of ingredients; spoon in pie shell.
Top with second crust.
Cut slits in top.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cube bread and place in melted butter; toss well.
In buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer half of the bread cubes, half Cheddar cheese, half of the broccoli, all of the cubed ham, then layer remaining broccoli, cheese and bread.
Beat eggs and milk thoroughly with seasoning.
Pour over all layers.
Refrigerate overnight or at least several hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until puffy and nicely browned.
Serves 6.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat eggs,
sugar,
oleo
and water until fluffy.
Sift flour, cocoa, soda and spices.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well. Fold
in
nuts,
apples, chips and vanilla.
Spoon into greased and floured
Bundt	pan
and bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes. Remove from
oven and let stand for 8 to 10 minutes. Place Bundt pan upside down on bottle and cool for 30 minutes.

title: parsley minute rice
directions: Chop green onions, bell peppers and parsley.
Add thinly sliced celery and shredded carrot; set aside.
Bring water, salt and butter to a boil.
Stir in rice and vegetable mixture.
Cover and remove from heat.
Allow to set for 5 minutes, then fluff with fork before serving.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: beef with orange flavor
directions: Mix beef with 1 tablespoon Hoison sauce and then toss with 2 tablespoons cornstarch and set aside.

title: noodles (homemade)
directions: Blend eggs, cream and salt.
Add flour gradually and work it in.
The dough should be stiff after the flour is worked in. Divide dough into 4 parts and roll very thin on a lightly floured board.
Let stand in air on a cloth to dry.
Turn every 15 minutes just until the edges start to crack slightly.
Place the 4 sheets one on top of each other.
Roll together tightly in jelly roll fashion.
Slice thick or thin as you wish.
After the roll has been cut, then cut the strips down the middle.
Boil in salted, oil water until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: south of the border corn bake(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in uncovered casserole on High 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: chunk chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat oleo, peanut butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls dough onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: see's fudge
directions: Place 6 tablespoons margarine, vanilla and chocolate chips in a large electric mixer bowl; set aside.
Melt remaining margarine and marshmallows in a double boiler.

Bring sugar and evaporated milk to a rolling boil for 7 to 8 minutes or to a soft ball stage. Pour margarine and melted marshmallows over ingredients in bowl. Add boiling sugar and milk; beat vigorously until creamy or 5 minutes with electric mixer.
Add chopped nuts and pour into 6 x 10-inch buttered dish.
Candy sets quickly.

title: oat bran cranberry muffins
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in one bowl.
Then in a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Fold ingredients together.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: cheesecake supreme
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Put 1/3 of dough on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan (sides removed).
Bake in hot oven at 400°
about 8 minutes or until golden.
Cool. Attach sides to bottom.
Butter and put remaining dough on sides to height of 1 3/4 inches.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels to make 1 cupful.
Mix with sugar and very soft butter.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; cool.
Mix softened cream cheese with sugar, then fold in Cool Whip.
Gently pat onto the cool crust.
Dissolve package of strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Add frozen strawberries.
When this begins to jell, spoon gently over cheese layer.
Refrigerate; cut into squares before serving.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk, sugar and salt.
Combine corn with remaining ingredients.
Combine with egg mixture; mix well. Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni casserole #3
directions: Cook
and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.	(You may want to sprinkle some grated cheese on top.)

title: baking mix
directions: Mix together and use in your favorite recipes as any store bought mix (Bisquick or Jiffy mix).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and English peas according to package directions, drain.
Add all ingredients together; fold in mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: nana's christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
eggs
and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Mix rest together and add to butter, sugar and eggs. Then add fruit and peel mixture last.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 375° from 7 to 10 minutes until done.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Divide eggs.
Beat yolks until light.
Add sugar, pinch of salt and juice of lemon.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool. Beat whites and add to cooled mixture.
Whip cream stiff; add to custard.
Crush fine the vanilla wafers.
Put half of the crumbs in bottom of dish.
Pour on custard.
Put other half of crumbs on top. Cover and freeze.
This can be kept for a long time in freezer. Take out 15 or 20 minutes before serving so you can cut it. Especially good for company since it can be made well in advance. Serves 6 to 8.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Take out yolks of all eggs.
Place in a bowl.
Take all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Amounts may be varied according to taste.
Once it's all whipped up, replace back into the white halves of the eggs.
Sprinkle a little paprika for color.
If more eggs are desired, then just increase other ingredients.

title: dry cooked spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large heavy pot with the water and soy sauce. Bring to boil over high heat.
Cover and reduce heat.
Allow ribs to simmer for 45 minutes.
Meanwhile mix together the wine and sugar.
At the end of the 45 minutes, remove the cover and turn the heat up high.
Add the sugar-wine mixture.
Stir the ribs occasionally.
The water will gradually evaporate.
Do not leave the pot once evaporation begins!
When water is gone, ribs will be be browning in own fat.
Be careful they do not burn.
Drain on paper towels.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Combine corn flakes, pepper and rosemary.
Dip chicken in milk; let excess drip off and roll in corn flakes.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with Pam so pieces aren't touching.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: vermont lima bean casserole
directions: Rinse lima beans; turn into large saucepan.
Add water; cover and soak for several hours or overnight.
When ready to cook, add onion.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes, uncovered.
Turn into a 3-quart casserole dish without draining.
Add remaining ingredients and cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 3 hours until beans are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients into large bowl.
Make a well in the middle.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake corn bread; cool.
Finely crumble into large mixing bowl. Add other ingredients into large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
Will keep several days.
Do not substitute salad dressing for real mayonnaise.

title: chocolate chip date nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine dates, soda and boiling water; set aside.
Cream together 1 cup sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add date mixture to creamed mixture.
Then gradually add flour, soda and salt.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nut meats. Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that is well greased and floured.

title: chicken breast in wine
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Put in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and salt.
Add mushrooms, water, soup and wine to butter left in skillet.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients together in a pan; put oleo, shortening, cocoa and water and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture and dissolve soda in milk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add to rest.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes in skins until almost done; chill slightly, then remove skins and grate potatoes into a large bowl.
In medium saucepan, combine 1/2 stick butter and cheese until almost melted. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper. Pour over potatoes.
Stir lightly and turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Can be made the day before and then baked.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Crush potato chips and mix with dressing.
Line bottom of buttered casserole with half of the chip mixture.
Layer corned beef, kraut and Swiss cheese.
Top with remaining chip mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with rye bread.
Reheatable.

title: nutty peach cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer all ingredients in ungreased cake pan.
Bake 55 minutes, or until top is golden brown.
Best served while warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Mix all together except 1/2 cup of cheese.
Mix with 2 forks until well mixed.
Pour in casserole dish; put remaining cheese over top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thick. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Gently blend in strawberries.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and lemon juice.
Spread on pie crust.
Add strawberry mixture.
Let cool thoroughly in refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: In casserole dish, mix together salsa, relish and 3/4's of the cheese.
In a small bowl, beat eggs.
Pour eggs on top of salsa mixture and spread rest of cheese on top of eggs and place in preheated oven at 400°
for 1/2 hour or until egg is cooked.
Mix well and eat hot with chops.
Enjoy.

title: pasta with chicken and sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet.
Add chicken and saute until brown and cooked through. Using slotted spoon, transfer chicken to a large bowl.
Keep warm.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender, about 6 minutes. Stir in carrot and sun-dried tomatoes. Saute until carrot is crisp-tender.
Transfer mixture to bowl with chicken.
Add pasta and Parmesan cheese.
Toss.
Serves 4.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Add to the date mixture in the skillet.
Keep hot while removing spoonfuls to shape into balls.
Then roll each cookie in coconut and powdered sugar.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: dilly salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into loaf.
Place in greased, shallow baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with Lemony Dill Sauce.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fluffy horseradish sauce
directions: Whip cream just to soft peaks; fold in horseradish and salt. Serve with beef, pork, burgers, ham or vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: cinnamon nuts
directions: Cook sugar and water until it spins a thread.
Add cinnamon, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until it sugars and nuts break apart.

title: tuna noodle and vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter and mix with drained peas. Break tuna with fork.
Combine butter, flour, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and milk.
Make a cream sauce.
Add 1 cup grated cheese.
Cook over low flame until cheese is melted.
Place peas, noodles and tuna in greased casserole and cover with cream sauce.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream together.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.

title: christie's apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat together the oil and sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to egg mixture and blend well.
Add vanilla and beat together well.
Stir in the apples, nuts and raisins.

title: crystallized peanuts
directions: Put all ingredients together in heavy saucepan and boil over medium heat until all liquid is evaporated.
Some stirring will be required when liquid becomes low to prevent peanuts from scorching and to make sugar crystallize.
When all liquid is gone and peanuts have a good coat of sugar on them, pour upon a large platter or cookie sheet and stir through with spoon once or twice to break peanuts apart.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine in large bowl.
Mix by hand until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cheese until light; add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes; turn onto cake rack to cool completely.

title: crock-pot brunswick stew
directions: Combine ground chuck with corn in crock-pot.
Mix well; add remaining ingredients to mix well.
Cook on low for 3 to 8 hours.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: *If using all-purpose flour, use one teaspoon salt and one teaspoon soda.

title: mom's soft sugar cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream sugar, butter, salt, yolks and whole eggs.
Dissolve baking soda in hot water.
Add, with the sour cream, to butter mixture.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture; dough will be sticky.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Let cool, then tear into small pieces.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Crumble crackers. Spread over melted butter, saving half of crackers for top.
Next, spread chicken pieces over crackers.
Take soups and add sour cream; mix all together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with remaining crackers and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew with its own gravy
directions: Place meat in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Cut vegetables into bite-sized pieces and place on top of meat. Sprinkle all dry ingredients over mixture.
Mix water and tomato juice and pour over stew.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours. Serve with hard rolls and salad.
Serves 4.

title: hobo burger
directions: Slice potatoes and place patty on tinfoil.
Cover all around with potato slices and bake at 425° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: i don't like rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix and let stand overnight rhubarb and sugar.
Following day, cook until done.
While warm, add jello and pineapple.
Chill and serve.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel carrots and slice into coin-shaped pieces. Cook until tender, but firm. Place in deep bowl. Add onion and pepper. Mix remaining ingredients with wire whisk and pour over carrot mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Makes 12 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco mix, sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on a cookie sheet and chill until ready to serve.
Cut up lettuce and tomato and layer on mixture.
Add cheese.
Ready to eat.
Dip your chips.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and place in baking dish. Mix together remaining 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll out and cut with small round cutter.
Cool a little and roll in powdered sugar.

title: date refrigerator pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick (10).
Add nuts and cool.
Work shortening with a spoon until fluffy and creamy; add brown sugar gradually while continuing to work.
Add the well beaten eggs and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, sifted together, and mix well.
Cover and chill.
Divide the mixture in 2 parts and roll each out separately into a rectangle a little less than 1/4-inch thick.
Spread each with some of the date filling and roll up as for jelly roll into 2 long rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill overnight if possible. Cut with a sharp knife into slices about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Chop vegetables, mix together and set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large pot, boil chicken until done.
Cool.
Reserve chicken broth.
Pull meat from bone; discard skin and set aside.
In large bowl, combine stuffing with reserved chicken broth.
Mixture should be moist, but not soupy.
Add soup, one can at a time; mix thoroughly.
Add mushrooms, onion and pepper, mixing well.
Add chicken.
(You may need to add more chicken broth.)
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese; mix well.
Pour mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish coated with vegetable spray.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 12 (1-cup) servings.

title: halibut veracruz(low-fat recipe)
directions: Place fish in shallow baking dish.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients; pour on top of fish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot and sour soup(meatless)
directions: Put it in the oven for 10 minutes and put it on the table into a bowl.
Get a spoon and stir it and eat it.
Finish it and wash your hands.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Form loaf and cook in 350° oven for approximately 1 hour, or form several small loaves and bake at 375°
for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix and beat zucchini, sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: apricot cranberry bread
directions: In large bowl combine flour, sugar, orange peel, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a small bowl, beat egg, water and oil.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in the cranberries.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Cut apricots in the preserves into small pieces.
Spoon preserves over the batter.
With a knife swirl.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan onto wire rack.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Grease 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish, set aside. Brown sausage and onion in medium skillet, drain well. Combine cornmeal, eggs, milk, corn and oil. Pour 1/2 of the batter into prepared skillet. Sprinkle with sausage and onion mixture and cheese. Pour remaining batter over top. Bake 30-40 minutes. Cool at least 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6-8.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt in saucepan butter or margarine, remove from heat.
Stir in confectioners sugar, peanut butter.
Using hands, shape into balls.
Combine in saucepan chocolate chips and paraffin.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Use toothpick and dip balls into mixture leaving a small portion uncovered.
Let stand on wax paper until set.

title: macaroni with cheese
directions: While macaroni is boiling, prepare the sauce as follows: In saucepan, melt butter slowly.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually and stir with a wooden spoon over moderate heat until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.

title: double coconut cream pie
directions: For Filling:
In a saucepan, combine the sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in the milk.
Cook until thickened.
In a bowl, beat the egg yolks with a fork; stir about 1 cup of the hot filling into yolks.
Return to saucepan; bring to a gentle boil. Cook and stir 2 more minutes.
Remove mixture from the heat.
Stir in 3/4 cup coconut, butter and vanilla.
Pour filling into baked pie crust.

title: trees and raisins salad
directions: Toss broccoli with next 3 ingredients.
Mix rest of ingredients and toss with broccoli mixture.

title: slow cooked sweet potato casserole
directions: Lightly butter crock-pot. Mix mashed sweet potatoes, margarine, sugar and light brown sugar together in a large bowl. Beat in juice, eggs and milk. Put in crock-pot.

title: wedding soup(minestra de scarola)
directions: Wash escarole under cold running water.
Be sure to open the leaves to get out any hidden grit.
Place a large size pot over medium-high heat.
Add water and escarole and boil for 10 minutes or until done.
Drain and allow to cool.
When cool, chop into small pieces and set aside.
While escarole is cooling, chop parsley into fine pieces and grate cheeses.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Put broccoli in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry, salt, pepper and paprika.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle cheese on top and buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into meat balls.
Brown meat balls in shortening. Drain when they are done.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie(mother's recipe)
directions: Boil first four ingredients until thickened.
Chill.
Combine with strawberries and place in pie shell.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: peach yogurt scones
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine Bisquick mix and 1/4 cup sugar.
Stir together the egg, the yogurt and melted butter.
Stir together just until the scone dough clings together.
Knead the dough gently on a floured surface for 8 to 10 strokes.
Pat or roll the scone dough to form a 6-inch circle.
Cut the dough into 10 wedges.
Sprinkle each of the wedges with sugar.
Place wedges on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Serve scones warm.
Can serve with favorite jelly or preserves.

title: slow-cooked swiss steak
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, mix the flour, salt, and pepper.
Add the steak; seal bag and toss to coat.
Place the onion in a greased slow cooker.
Top with the steak, celery, and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 6 - 8 hours.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine Bisquick, sugar and spices.
Lightly beat egg and mix with milk.
Add melted butter and pumpkin to milk and egg. Combine wet and dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Fill greased or papered muffin cups 2/3 full and bake in 375° to 400° oven for 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 12 to 16 muffins.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until tender; drain.
Saute onions in half the butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Mix 1 1/2 cups stuffing, onions, soup and sour cream; stir in the zucchini.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining stuffing and melted butter.
Toss gently over top of casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued short ribs of beef
directions: Melt butter; add onion.
Cook until clear.
Add dry seasonings, ketchup, sauces, vinegar and water and bring to a boil.
Have short ribs cut into serving size pieces.
Brown thoroughly.
Place in pan and pour barbecue sauce over ribs. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover last 15 minutes of cooking.
Baste ribs and finish cooking.

title: pecan nut roll
directions: Mix all together and roll out in 1 large roll or 4 small rolls.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels with Eagle Brand milk in double boiler to a liquid.
Mix in pecans.
Spoon onto buttered cookie sheet.
Place in freezer for about 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate and paraffin. Dip candy in this and place on waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.

title: microwave crumb-coated chicken
directions: In small bowl beat together eggs, butter and salt. In shallow dish place crumbs.
Coat chicken with crumbs.
Then coat with egg mixture and then crumbs again. In 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish arrange chicken with meatiest pieces to outer side edges of dish and cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High 18 to 22 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 10 minutes, until done.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, melted butter, and onions in a bowl.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Spread potato mixture in dish. Cover with cheese.
Mix soup and sour cream; cover the layer of cheese.
Mix corn flakes with melted butter and place on top.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: miss birdie's coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix everything and pour into two unbaked pie shells and cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: pot roast with carrots and potatoes
directions: You will also need 1 cooking bag.

title: immune system booster broth
directions: J. D. wrote this recipe in his kindergarten class at age 6: Cook bread in a frying pan.
Cut out a circle.
Crack an egg in it. Turn it over two times.
The egg sticks on the toast so you cut it.

title: poke sallet
directions: Saute bacon until crisp, remove from drippings and set aside to drain.
Parboil poke greens and drain.
Add poke and soy sauce to hot bacon drippings.
Simmer, tightly covered, until poke is wilted.
Drop eggs individually on poke.
Cook, covered, until eggs are firm.
Using spatula, cut around each egg and place on warm plates.
Crumble bacon pieces over eggs and serve.
Serves 2.

title: mother's sour cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a Bundt pan.
Using a mixer, beat the butter with the granulated sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks and blend well into the butter mixture.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° in middle rack of oven for 30 minutes. Rotate and pierce with fork.
Bake additional 30 minutes.
Slice small lid from top of potato and scoop out potato.
(Leave enough potato as not to see skin.)
Salt inside of remaining potato.
Add to scooped out potato the scallions, sour cream, butter, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Spoon filling into potato boats.
Top with Cheddar cheese and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(You may add bacon, ham, broccoli, etc., to filling.)

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Butter and flour a 9-inch pie pan.
Set the oven at 350°. Beat egg whites.
Beat in, a spoonful at a time, the sugar.
Add vanilla. Mix together graham cracker crumbs, baking powder, salt, shredded coconut and chopped walnuts.
Spread in the pan and bake 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in ovenproof dish.
If desired, sprinkle 1/3 cup slivered almonds over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first four (4) ingredients together.
Shape into balls (walnut size).
Place on wax paper, refrigerate at least two (2) hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture using toothpick or cake tester.
Place on wax paper.
Cool.
Put in airtight container; refrigerate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water. Add blueberries and pineapple with juice.
Pour into bowl and put in refrigerator to jel.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Steam or boil carrots and drain.
Mix all ingredients and cover in refrigerator for at least 12 hours.
Serve as a salad over greens or as a cold salad dish.

title: tuna buns
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together.
Split
buns and spread mixture on the bun.
Wrap
in
foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
May be frozen.
A good Lenten meal.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Wash chicken.
Pat somewhat dry.
Season chicken with all spices.
Cover all chicken parts with paprika.
Place in casserole or roasting pan with lid.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover pan with lid and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve.

title: cheese broccoli
directions: Thaw broccoli and drain well.
Saute onion in 4 tablespoons of margarine.
Stir in flour.
Add water; cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add salt.
Blend in cheese.
Combine sauce and broccoli and eggs and mix gently until blended.
Turn into greased casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken in red pepper sauce
directions: Skin and cut chicken into chunks. Puree onions, ginger, almonds, peppers, cumin, coriander, turmeric, cayenne and salt. Add a little water to break down, if necessary.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix according to directions.
Drizzle with Kahlua.
Cut or break brownie into pieces.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water until done.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Cook noodles in chicken broth until tender; drain broth.
Cook onion in oil until done.
Add deboned chicken to noodles.
Add onion and soups together and mix with noodles and chicken.
Put into casserole dish.
Top with cheese and then cracker crumbs.
Put into moderate oven until cheese is melted.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by directions in sheet pan. Crumble when done. Make layers in bowl of 1/2 each ingredient, starting with cake. Then start over and use second half of each ingredient. Very pretty in glass bowl.

title: baked fruit cocktail
directions: In 6-cup baking dish combine sugar and flour.
Add cocktail with liquid and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine brown sugar and nuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange chops and rice tango
directions: Season chops with 1 envelope of broth, black pepper and ginger.
In large skillet, brown chops.
Remove chops and drain excess fat.
Stir in onion and saute lightly.
Stir in water, orange juice, catsup, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt and remaining chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and place chops on top.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in a greased baking dish.
Melt butter and sugar together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, basting occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: barbecued loin of pork
directions: Roast pork in shallow pan at 325° about 45 minutes.
One half hour before meat is done, pour off drippings.
Combine soup and remaining ingredients to make sauce.
Pour over meat.
Continue roasting.
Spoon sauce over meat often.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and milk.
Beat smooth.
Heat oil in skillet. Pour mixture into funnel.
Release into hot oil.
Cook about 2 minutes or until golden brown.
Take out of oil.
Place on a paper towel.
Let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and top with cherry pie filling.

title: egg and ham bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt oleo, put half in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Beat eggs; season with salt and pepper.
Add ham, cheese, flour mixture and other half of oleo.
Mix, pour into dish, bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°, bake 30 minutes longer or until puffy and light golden brown.
Can be mixed and stored in refrigerator until ready to be baked.
Can also be baked and frozen.

title: butterfly lamb
directions: Marinate a boned and butterflied leg of lamb at least overnight (up to 48 hours).
Barbecue over hot coals for 45 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: rice consomme
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Mix together. Pour into cupcake pan in paper cupcake holders. Freeze.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Soak
brisket
overnight
in 1/2 bottle liquid smoke in covered
dish
in refrigerator.
Next morning, pour off liquid smoke
and
pour
bottle
Worcestershire sauce over meat. Season
with
salt,
pepper, onion and celery salt.
Cover and bake for 5 hours at 275°.
When done, pour off most of liquid. Cover meat
with
barbecue
sauce;
cover with foil and bake 1 hour more.
(If
desired,
you can add 1/4 to 1/2 cup water at this time.)

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef. Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients, stirring after each.
Bring to a boil then reduce heat to a simmer and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: peanut blossom cookies
directions: Cream first four ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine with other mixture.
Shape into balls and dip in white sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Press in candy kisses.
Return to bake 2 to 5 minutes.

title: stollen(german christmas bread)
directions: Scald milk; stir in shortening, sugar, salt and lemon rind. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk mix, eggs and 1 cup flour to yeast mix.
Beat thoroughly.
Add fruit. Stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down, turn out on board.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Roll into oval 3/4 inch thick.
Brush 1/2 of oval with butter. Fold over.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise until double, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Spread icing on lightly.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: red apple rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over butter, sugar and salt; let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water; beat in eggs.
Add to the cooled butter mixture.
Add flour; mix well.
Let sit overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Shape 2 hours before baking.
Melt butter or margarine and brush onto tops as rolls are shaped.
Sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed if desired.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.

title: buford's fish bake
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter.
Add salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Place fish steaks on foil in baking pan.
Pour seasoned sauteed sauce over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until blended and heated thoroughly.
Serve dip hot, with chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Dip wafers in milk and layer bottom of pan.
Make pudding using 4 cups milk instead of three.
Cut bananas in slices. Layer on top of wafers.
Keep layering until pan is full.
Pour pudding over the layers. Whip egg whites and add sugar. Spread over top.
Turn oven on, put pan in and brown top.

title: arizona casserole
directions: Brown and drain the ground meat, garlic and onion.
Add the tomato sauce, sugar, black olives, green chilies and chili powder; heat through until well blended.
Layer as follows:
meat mixture, cottage cheese with eggs, grated cheese and softened tortillas. Continue layers; end with meat and cheese so tortillas won't dry out.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
This recipe makes a large casserole, more than will go in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Great for large groups!

title: all-day oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine meat, veggies and potatoes in 3-quart casserole.
Mix tomato puree, salt, pepper and cornstarch. Pour into casserole.
Stir, cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake the cake mix by box and cook in a rectangular pan.
When done, punch lots of holes in cake.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together.
Pour this over the cake while still hot. Mix the sour cream, frozen coconut and confectioners sugar together.
Pour over cake after it slightly cools. Top cake with flaked coconut and pecan pieces.

title: pork marinade
directions: Mix and pour over pork, cut in small pieces.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dan dan mien
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain, rinse with cold water, drain again and toss with 1 tablespoon sesame seed oil.
Set aside.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Make the cake mix as directed in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool. Punch holes all over the cake.
Mix the condensed milk and cream of coconut. Spread over slightly warm cake.
Refrigerate overnight. Frost with the Cool Whip. Sprinkle white or tinted coconut on top.

title: pizza muffins
directions: In 2 tablespoons oil, saute onion and garlic.
In a bowl, mix sauteed mixture with tomato juice and egg.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, oregano and 1 cup of cheese. Quickly stir wet ingredients until moistened.
Spoon into oiled muffin cups, and sprinkle tops with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add zucchini and shallots. Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring often, until zucchini is soft but not browned.
Combine half the zucchini mixture, 2 cups of broth, curry powder, salt and cayenne.
Puree in blender.
Repeat pureeing with remaining ingredients.
Combine batches.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and water.

title: john's vegetarian "ska-betti"
directions: In your biggest pan, saute in olive oil the onion.
Add fresh garlic, basil, oregano, cinnamon and cloves.
Add cubed vegetables, sauteing rapidly over high heat.
Add sliced tomatoes and red wine (we just fill the pan up with tomatoes).
Once this is bubbling nicely, turn down to medium heat and let liquids boil down about 30 minutes, with lid off.
About 10 minutes before dinner, boil the spaghettini until done.
Rinse and serve with sauce.
Leftover sauce freezes well for future meals.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk. Fold in fruit.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil sweet potatoes (in the skins) until soft.
Peel as soon as you can handle them.
Mix in egg yolks, margarine, pineapple and sugar.
(Save egg whites for meringue.)
Place in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in a greased 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Rub together flour, sugar and butter.
Drop over apples and bake for 45 minutes.

title: salmon mousse with cucumber sauce
directions: Combine salmon and dry mustard.
Set aside. In top of double boiler, mix the sugar, flour, salt and pepper.
Ad the beaten egg yolks, melted butter, milk and vinegar.
Cook over boiling water until thick.
Dissolve gelatin in 3 tablespoons of cold water. Add to mixture.
Cook 1 more minute, stirring constantly.
Add salmon mixture.
Place in 1 quart mold and chill.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and magarine until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat and cool 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oats.
Stir well and drop on wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli as package directs.
Roll crackers and melt butter.
Layer broccoli and chicken in casserole dish.
Put crackers on top and bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: suzie's taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with taco chips.

title: russian chicken
directions: Mix onion soup mix, Russian dressing and apricot preserves together.
Pour the dressing mixture over chicken, using 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is completely cooked.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Pat into a large pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Dressing will be thick. Store in tightly covered jar in refrigerator.
Stir well before using.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Combine yeast and water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine milk, sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, yeast mixture and half of the flour.
Beat 2 minutes on electric mixer (medium speed).
Add remaining flour and vanilla.
Beat 2 more minutes with a spoon.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add stuffing mix and coat.
Mix in bowl 1 3/4 cups stuffing mix, broth, chicken, soup, onion and peas.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and put 3/4 cup stuffing mix on top.
Bake in a 425° ove for 35 minutes.
I bake mine in a glass dish and reduce the heat to 400°.
