I also cover the dish with aluminum foil and take off foil for the last 5 to 10 minutes to brown.

title: pineapple waffle sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and cook until heated thoroughly.
This can be served hot or cold over waffles or pancakes along with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugars and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Add sugar gradually.
Add nuts.
Beat on low speed until well blended.
Spoon out onto wax paper.
Let stand 12 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 bread loaf pans.

title: lemonade(easy way)
directions: In large, heat-safe pitcher, put lemon slices, sugar and boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Chill until cold. To serve, pour over ice cubes in chilled tall glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Beat in Eagle Brand until smooth. Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla. Slice bananas in mixture. Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Drain salmon and mix with other ingredients.
Drop in hot corn oil.
Turn when brown and let brown on other side.
The cakes should be soft in the middle.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve while hot.
(If cooked in a T-Fal pan, you can use very little oil.)

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Poke holes across cake as a jello cake.
Pour crushed pineapple over top and spoon juice into holes. Cool cake.
Mix pudding and milk and add to Cool Whip. Beat about 2 minutes. Spread over cool cake.
Sprinkle coconut over top, if desired.

title: carol's baked twice potato casserole
directions: Peel, boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in cream cheese, butter or margarine and sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Put potatoes in pan.
Sprinkle top with both cheeses and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or until heated through.

title: cheese-broccoli-brunch surprise
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Place half the bread slices in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with layers of cheese, broccoli and ham.
Top with remaining bread. Mix eggs, milk, salt, onions and mustard; pour over bread.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 55 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook fryer until tender.
Cool and debone.
Cook onion and celery in small amount of water.
Add chestnuts and bamboo shoots in small amount of broth.
Cook cabbage; don't overcook.
Add all salt, pepper and soy sauce to taste.
Cook rice in broth.
Serve as side dish or with chow mein.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Use a microwave bowl.
Place in bowl as listed, except nuts. Cook on High for 5 minutes.
Take out of microwave and stir all together.
Add nuts and mix approximately 5 minutes.
Pour in pan. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut as wanted.

title: kraut and wieners
directions: Put kraut in pan.
Add wieners, cut in slices.
Cook on medium until wieners are done.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in electric skillet using oil or spray to grease skillet. Cover pork chops with tomatoes, tomato sauce and rice.
Cover with water, just barely. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Salt to taste. Serve with tossed salad and hot buttered bread.

title: punch for 50 people
directions: Pour boiling water over citric acid in large earthen bowl.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Then mix sugar, pineapple juice, orange juice and cold water.
Chill and serve.

title: torte
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla on high speed for 20 minutes. Fold in by hand the flour and baking powder.

title: green cucumber pickles(three day sweet)
directions: Place lime in water; add cucumbers.
Soak for 24 hours, then soak for four hours in clear water, changing every hour.

title: red and green coleslaw
directions: Combine oil, sugar and vinegar in small, non-aluminum saucepan.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Simmer for 5 minutes and add celery seed, mustard, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In small mixer bowl, combine 2 tablespoons butter, cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, egg, 3 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat at high speed.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend well; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over batter, spreading carefully to cover.
Top with remaining batter and spread to cover.
Do not mix batters.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and frost (also good with powdered sugar instead of frosting).

title: cilantro dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour dressing over; mix again.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: aunt ella's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease casserole dish.
Cook macaroni, drain and return to pan.
Stir in butter and egg.
In large bowl, combine mustard, salt and nutmeg with a tablespoon boiling water.
Stir in milk, 2 1/2 cups cheese, onion and macaroni.

title: tortellini vegetable toss
directions: Combine broccoli, mushrooms, tomatoes, zucchini, tortellini and olives.
Add combined dressing and mustard.
Mix lightly. Chill.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: In frying pan, combine shortening, squash, onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until done.
Drain well.
Pour in casserole dish. Cool about 15 minutes.
Beat eggs, then stir into squash and onions.
Put cheese on top of squash.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over cheese.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hopping john
directions: Cook black-eyed peas according to directions on package. Drain.
Meantime, fry bacon, crisp; remove from pan.
Fry onions until golden in the fat.
Add, with fat, to rice and water.
Bring to the boil and cook until water is absorbed (about 15 minutes). When almost done, add drained peas and let them heat.
Serves 6.

title: papaya or mango salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients well and allow to sit, refrigerated, for at least 1 hour.
You may make salsa ahead of serving time but only by 24 hours or less.

title: spicy corn and black bean relish
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn, beans and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl; pour over corn mixture and toss to coat.
Chill. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Clean and cut peppers.
Put in ice water overnight.
Boil water, vinegar, sugar and salt for five minutes.
In quart jars, put 1 clove garlic and peppers.
Seal as for canning.
Boil 3 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: stuffed zucchini with italian sausage
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place washed whole zucchini in large pot of boiling water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Remove zucchini and cut each in half lengthwise.
Scoop out most of pulp, leaving a shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Chop the pulp coarsely.

title: marinara sauce de bella napoli
directions: In 2 large bowls, separate the juice from the plum tomatoes; put on the side.
In a large saucepan, pour in olive oil.
Turn heat on medium-high.
Chop up a good amount of fresh parsley and saute in olive oil with garlic cloves until garlic is golden color. Turn heat down to low and let cool a little.
Crush the plum tomatoes with hands until considerably crushed into smaller pieces. Put in pot with olive oil and garlic.
Turn up heat to medium-high again and fry for approximately 15 minutes.
Lower heat again to medium-low.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Pour in juice from tomatoes.
Add remaining parsley, lots of basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on medium-low for approximately 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently (don't let tomatoes stick to bottom of pot).

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix and spoon over chicken pieces.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: saucy franks with rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Reserve 1 tablespoon drippings and saute onion, green pepper, celery, and garlic until tender in saved drippings.
Add bacon.
Add pineapple juice, catsup, and chili powder.
Bring to a boil.
Add cut up hot dogs or smokies and simmer covered 5-8 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: tahitian pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet and place in baking dish.
Put all other ingredients into blender and mix until smooth.
Pour over chops; bake at 375°, covered with foil, for 45 minutes, turning once.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients except soda which has been dissolved in hot water.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake in greased muffin pan in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners (10x) sugar.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, 2/3 of Cool Whip, sour cream and nutmeg. Layer bananas and vanilla wafers ending with pudding mix.
Add remainder of Cool Whip on top.

title: mandarin orange dessert
directions: Cook tapioca, pudding, jello and water all together; boil and thicken.
Remove from stove to cool 1/2 hour.
Add oranges and Cool Whip.
Beat all together and chill.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Work together with fingers until mealy, like pie crust.
Add boiling water, approximately 1 1/2 cups.
Stir until it's cool enough to use hands to mix.
Add more water until it looks like bread dough.
Knead in bowl, adding more flour as needed.
Cover with towel to rest and rise, 1/2 to 1 hour.
Separate into pieces about the size of a plum.
Roll dough (room temperature) and cook on hot iron skillet, 30 to 45 seconds on each side.
Keep tortillas warm between towels until all are cooked.

title: oatmeal cake and topping
directions: Pour water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream sugars, shortening and oats.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour gradually, then add nuts and vanilla.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Before cookies cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: banana bread
directions: Put all in a large bowl and mix with large spoon.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions; drain and refrigerate.
In a medium bowl, combine peas, tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Mix well.

title: glazed apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, apricot nectar and salad oil in large bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Pour batter into greased, floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on rack, right side up, for 15 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: steamed shrimp
directions: Remove heads from shrimp.
Rinse and put into heavy pot.

Add oil, vinegar, cut up orange (rind and all), cut up lemon (rind and all), onion, sprinkle of garlic and salt and crab boil to taste. Simmer slowly, stirring occasionally, with cover on pot, until shrimp are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: chinatown almond chicken
directions: Bone and cube chicken breasts.
Heat oil; stir in almonds. Cook and stir about 3 minutes.
Add chicken and cook just until meat turns white.
Mix ginger, sugar, sherry, water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Pour over chicken and heat until thickened.
Add thawed vegetables and stir-fry just until glazed.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Blend drained pineapple; fold in bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (greased).
Serves 6.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over mixed vegetables.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Drain a little before serving.
Salad will keep in Frigidaire for several weeks.

title: mother's fudge
directions: Grease platter.
Place sugar, chocolate and milk in pan.
As soon as pan is put on medium heat, begin stirring and stir continuously until a soft ball can be formed when chocolate is dropped in cold water.
Add a dash of salt while cooking.
It only takes a few minutes (about 10) to get to soft ball stage.
Then place pan with spoon in place cold water and let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Add 3/4 stick butter and vanilla and stir until right consistency (at least 10 minutes).
Then pour into greased platter. Let set and cut into squares.
Freezes well or keep in tin.

title: corn bread
directions: Bake in muffin pans at 400° until brown.

title: tuna cheese flips
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In bowl, mix tuna (drained), lemon pepper, cheese, salad dressing, celery and onion.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Press or roll each into a 5-inch circle.
Spoon about 1/4 cup tuna mixture onto the center of each biscuit.
Fold dough in half over filling; press edges with fork to seal.
Brush each biscuit with egg or milk.
Press both sides in crushed chips. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make 2 or 3 (1/2-inch) slits in each top crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 24 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Makes 10 sandwiches.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Melt 1 cup mint morsels.*

title: mom's old fashioned applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat together.
Add apples that soda has been added to.
Coat raisins and nuts with flour, then add flour and spices.
Beat together good.
Bake in four 9-inch pans at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cream 2 sticks butter or margarine and 2 cups flour to which pepper has been mixed.
Add cheese and Rice Krispies.
Form into balls.
Press flat with fork.
Bake on foil sheets for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and pumpkin. Alternate dry ingredients and milk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious plain or topped with cream cheese frosting.

title: layered enchiladas
directions: Simmer ground beef and onion with chili powder, salt and pepper until onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Dip tortillas in enchilada sauce and layer as follows:
tortilla, ground beef, cheese;
tortilla, ground beef, cheese;
end with tortilla and top with cheese.
Pour remaining sauce over enchilada.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Cover and chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir well and serve with cut up vegetables, chips or bread cubes.

title: homemade soap
directions: Grease from any kind of meat or frying oil which has been used or commercial shortening, lard, etc. can be used.

title: my original pimento cheese
directions: Have cheese at room temperature, then grate.
Beat with mixer after you add mayonnaise.
Beat until smooth.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Beat until smooth again.
Put in refrigerator and chill.

title: pain perdu(lost bread)
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
When well mixed, add cornstarch.
Let bread soak in mixture and fry until light brown.
Serve with butter and syrup.

title: pumpkin doughnuts
directions: Cream sugar, pumpkin spice, dry milk and shortening.
Add egg yolk.
Add pumpkin, cake flour, flour and baking powder.
Mix until well blended, then let dough set 10 minutes.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter and fry in deep fat at 385°.
Makes about 4 dozen doughnuts.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and water.
Mix with remaining ingredients well; set overnight to marinate good.
Good for weeks; keep in refrigerator.

title: strietzel
directions: Heat water and milk to 130°.
Mix yeast, salt, sugar, oil, egg and half of the flour in bowl.
Drizzle heated liquids into the bowl, mixing with a beater until smooth.
Stir in lemon rind, juice and raisins.
Stir/knead in remaining flour, until dough is smooth and elastic.
Rise until doubled, knead and shape.
Loaves may be shaped in rounds or braided.
Rise until doubled; brush with 1 beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, depending on size of loaves.

title: pastry mix
directions: Mix egg with milk; cut shortening, sugar, salt and baking powder with flour, then add to milk mixture.
Knead on floured surface.
Makes 5 large pie shells or about 20 regular fried pie shells.

title: mandarin pineapple cake
directions: Beat together cake mix, oil and eggs.
Add Mandarin oranges and juice.
Beat together.
Bake in 3 layers, greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° until done, about 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: norma's beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together in covered 3-quart casserole. Cook in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve on rice or noodles. Uncover last 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken cutlets with roasted red peppers
directions: Wash and dry chicken cutlets.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on both sides and dip them in flour to coat lightly.
Heat the oil in a nonstick frying pan.
Brown the cutlets lightly on both sides on medium high heat.
Do not overcook.

title: corn bread cake
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Cook 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pork
directions: Combine the soy sauce, pineapple juice and brown sugar; pour over the pork and marinate.
Bake pork in mixture until done.
Add the pineapple chunks, cherries and green pepper until warmed.
Use the mixture over rice.
(The marinade is also good with chicken.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and arrange in a shallow 1 1/2 or 2 quart casserole.
Simmer chicken until tender, approximately 25 minutes.
Drain, break up and arrange over broccoli.
Mix next four ingredients and pour over the top of the chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: molded egg ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over water in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat over moderately low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: turkey frame soup
directions: Place turkey frame in large Dutch oven with water, onion, and salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Remove turkey frame; cool till it can be handled.
Remove meat from bones; discard bones.
Remove onion from broth.
Stir in fresh vegetables.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
If desired, add homemade noodles or packaged egg noodles; simmer uncovered 8 to 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Can freeze leftovers.
Makes 12 servings.

title: homemade bread
directions: In a saucepan, scald milk and add hot water. Add margarine, sugar and salt. Stir to combine. Remove from heat and cool until lukewarm. In a bowl, soften yeast in 1/2 cup hot water. Add 6 cups flour to yeast; beat with a spoon until smooth. Add remaining 6 cups of flour. Turn out on a floured board. Knead dough about 7 to 10 minutes while continuing to sprinkle with flour. Put dough in a large greased bowl and turn dough over to coat with oil from bowl. Cover bowl with a kitchen towel and let rise until doubled, about 2 hours. Turn dough out onto counter and cut into 4 loaves. Put each loaf in a loaf pan and let rise again for about an hour. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 minutes. Makes 4 loaves.

title: frosted pecans(great for nibbling)
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Set aside.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Gradually add sugar until mixture is thick and smooth.
Take time doing this, so meringue has body.
Fold in pecans until they are thoroughly coated.
Drop mixture by spoonfuls into pan with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Every 10 minutes, gently turn and separate the nuts, using a small spatula so they are brown and evenly covered with butter.
Cool in pan.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until it starts to boil.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Continue boiling until crystallizes or until all the syrup is off the bottom of the pan.
Put on greased cookie sheet and separate.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all seasonings.
Drain grease off. Add tomato paste and water.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese together.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Fold in oats, then corn flakes and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake 7 to 8 minutes or until brown at 350°.
Makes a dishpan full!

title: cherry fluff
directions: Whip chilled milk and add powdered sugar.
Drain pineapple; heat juice and necessary water to dissolve Jell-O.
Add cream cheese; beat until dissolved.
Cool.
Add and fold into whipped cream.
Chill in refrigerator and serve.

title: sugar topped muffins
directions: Combine
all
ingredients;
pour into muffin tins.
Top with cinnamon
and
sugar
before baking at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. You
can also pour batter into a 9 x 9-inch cake pan for a coffee cake.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown ground beef with salt, pepper and brown sugar.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Layer ground beef mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish with process cheese between layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Mix brown sugar, vanilla, butter and eggs in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls, about 3 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Press 3 to 4 additional candies into each cookie if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until light brown. Cool slightly, remove to wire rack.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Simmer tomatoes, tomato paste, onion, green pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt for 20 minutes.
Shape meat into 1-inch balls and brown in fat in skillet.
Mix flour with 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Thoroughly coat eggplant slices in flour mixture.
Heat 1/4 cup vegetable oil in large skillet.
Lightly brown eggplant slices on both sides.
Add oil as needed.
Spread a thin layer of tomato mixture over bottom of 3-quart rectangular baking dish. Arrange half of the eggplant on bottom.
Top with half remaining sauce and half of each cheese.
Repeat.
Arrange meat balls on top.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour until hot and bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat shortening in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix Potato Buds, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken parts in egg and then mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain fat, then add tomato paste, Sloppy Joe mix and ketchup.
Cook 10 minutes.
About halfway through cooking, add chili powder.
Then, layer meat, jalapeno, cheese and continue and finish with cheese.

title: glazed cereal meat loaf
directions: Mix currant jelly with mustard and brush over meat loaf.
Cook another 25 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix chicken, soups and milk.
Heat flour tortillas in microwave wrapped in paper towel for 1 minute. Put about 2 large spoonfuls of mixture in tortilla shell and roll. Place in pan with seam down.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Boil water and vinegar.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and eggs in a bowl. Add to water and vinegar. Boil until stiff and add mustard. Add equal parts of Miracle Whip and dressing and put on potato salad.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda and add.
Add 3 cups quick oats, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Mix together.
Chill.
Roll in balls and then roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 375` for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: golden puff donuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add liquid ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil or shortening.
Fry until brown on one side. Turn and fry until other side is brown.
Drain on paper towels. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pudding layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix melted margarine with flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: orange milk shake
directions: When you buy fresh ginger root, it is best to put into a jar with a lid. Cover with vodka or white wine.
It can be left in refrigerator for months.
The ginger root will be ready to grate for stir-fries or any other recipe calling for fresh ginger.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly. Stir in applesauce.
Add sifted flour and all other dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and let stand.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour into a greased pan. Pour first mixture over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and use tablespoon to slice down into liquid in bottom of dish.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: tropical waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Refrigerate.
This salad is wonderful for holiday meals, for company or harried days.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil. Sprinkle with flour and brown. Add remaining ingredients, except mushrooms. Cover and simmer slowly for 2 1/2 hours. Add mushrooms in last 15 minutes. Serve over plain or wild rice.

title: beef with wine
directions: In large casserole dish, layer meat, mushrooms, onion soup mix and celery soup, then wine.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: shaun's favorite coffee cake
directions: This recipe must be prepared the night before, so it requires planning ahead.

title: sea island tuna salad
directions: Cook Creamettes according to directions on package.
Drain and chill.
Stir in mayonnaise blended with sour cream and seasonings. Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Do not brown ground chuck.
Cook at least 2 hours.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk (enough to make a stiff dough).
Roll out on lightly floured surface to a very thin layer. Cut into squares.
Drop dumplings (a few at a time) into boiling chicken broth.
Sprinkle with pepper.

title: vegetable noodle soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine water, tomato sauce and vegetables. Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes. Stir in Lipton noodle soup mix and chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: ty's chicken or turkey with fresh spinach salad for two(low-fat)
directions: For Sauce:
Stir together water, cornstarch and bouillon.
Set aside.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients together until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Add 1 or more pints chicken broth.
Put all in a large casserole. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes, covered. Add shredded cheese sprinkled on top. If more liquid needed, add to casserole before adding cheese.
Cook uncovered after adding cheese. Cook until cheese is bubbly.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes. Meanwhile, fry bacon until it is crisp and set aside.

title: cheese covered dates
directions: Mix butter, cheese, salt, pepper and flour.
Take a ball of the mixture and wrap around a pitted date.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 33 balls.

title: creamy succotash
directions: Cook lima beans, covered, in the water seasoned with salt and pepper for 10 minutes.
Add frozen corn.
Return to boiling. Reduce heat; cover and cook 5 minutes more or until tender.
Do not drain.
Gradually stir milk into flour; stir into vegetable mixture in saucepan.
Add butter or margarine.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Add pumpkin.
Mix well. Add the baking soda.
Add the flour a little at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Fill regular size bread pans half full and bake at 350 for 1 to 1-1/2 hours or until a knife comes out clean.
Batter can be baked in 5-6 mini loaf pans.
Baking time for mini-loaf pans is about 40-50 minutes.

title: old suzanna pie
directions: Bake pie crust on low heat; melt margarine.
Add coconut and pecans.
Stir until toasted lightly brown.
Set aside.

title: onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter until golden brown.
Add water and bouillon; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Place soup in 6 ovenproof soup bowls.
Top each serving with a bread slice and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: dad's cabbage rolls
directions: Cut out the core of each head of cabbage and stick a large fork into the space where the core was.
Roll the cabbage back and forth in a large pot of boiling water to loosen leaves.
Remove leaves, slice off the rib on each leaf and place leaves in warm water. Should have 20 to 30 leaves.
Combine next 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix until it starts to fluff up, about 5 to 10 minutes. Spoon a small amount (approximately 1/4 cup) on each leaf, fold in the sides and roll.
Place, seam side down, in a large ovenproof pot.
Add a mixture of 70% tomato juice and 30% water to about 1/4 inch from covering the rolls.
Place pot on burner and bring to a hard boil.
Place pot in 400° oven for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to 325° and let simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
You may add carrots and potatoes if you wish.

title: macaroni and cheese(microwave)
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart casserole dish and melt.
Add salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes or until thick.
Stir several times during last half of cooking time to prevent lumping.
Stir in cheese. Add cooked macaroni.
Cover with tight fitting lid or plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium for 12 to 15 minutes or until heated throughout, stirring halfway through cooking time.

title: cran-orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions, using chilled juice from pineapple as part of cool water.
Mix the rest in and chill.

title: summer casserole
directions: Cook squash, onion and zucchini until tender. Add salt and pepper to taste. Beat egg. Add milk, cracker crumbs and cheese. Drain squash mixture. Add 3 tablespoons butter. Add to egg mixture. Put in casserole. Sprinkle with extra cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add soup, tomatoes, beans and sauce.
Add enough water to make it soupy if desired.

title: stuffed cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice bread lengthwise three-quarters of the way through the middle.
Scoop out the soft part of the bread and reserve for another use.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend well. Stuff into hollowed bread.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake for 20 minutes.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices and serve.
Garnish with soups or salads.

title: chicken stuffing
directions: In a large saucepan, mix water, margarine, stuffing and gravy until well mixed.
Layer 1/2 stuffing mixture in casserole and add diced chicken.
Then add rest of stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach crazy pie
directions: First, melt butter in baking dish.
Next, mix flour, milk and sugar together.
Pour into dish.
Lastly, place fruit on top of mixture.
Cover dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Peel apples and cut into thick slices.
Arrange apples in pie pan lined with pastry.
Sprinkle on lemon juice.
Mix sugar, spices and flour together; cut in oleo until crumbly.
Spoon over apples; spread sour cream on the top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly brown onion in oil.
Add all other ingredients, except frankfurters.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Split frankfurters.
Place in baking dish.
Pour barbecue sauce over frankfurters.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, basting several times.

title: hawaiian icebox cake(low-fat)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; beat at low speed of an electric mixer 30 seconds.
Increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake springs back when touched lightly in center. Let cool in pan on a wire rack.
Combine milk and pudding mix in a medium bowl; beat at low speed of electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened. Cover and chill 5 minutes.
Stir in pineapple.
Pierce 48 holes in top of cake, using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Spread pudding mixture over cake and then spread whipped topping over pudding mixture.
Sprinkle topping with shredded coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield:
16 servings.
Serving size:
1 (3 1/4 x 2 1/4-inch) piece.
Calories:
Fat grams:
Preparation time:
17 minutes.
Cooking time:
35 minutes.

title: parmesan pita triangles
directions: Heat boiler, split pita bread horizontally.
Cut each 1/2 into 4 pieces.
Place on baking sheet.
Spread with margarine.
Add cheese; broil until brown.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients.
Chill after mixed.
Roll and cut into desired shapes.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Ice with thin confectioners sugar icing while hot.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Add sugar to egg whites.
Continue to beat until very stiff. Fold in chocolate chips.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies in oven and turn off.
Leave in oven for 8 hours or overnight.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Grease and flour 1 large loaf pan.
Ste oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat eggs, sugar, 1/2 cup zucchini, oil and vanilla. Sift in flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder; beat.
Add 1/2 cup zucchini and beat.
Add well-drained pineapple and walnuts; stir to mix.
Add to loaf pan and bake 1 hour.
Test.

title: buckaroo beans
directions: Wash beans; bring the 6 cups water to boiling.
Add the washed beans and boil about 2 minutes.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand one hour.
This is equal to 10 to 12 hours soaking time in cold water.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour peaches in pie shell.
Mix sugar and flour well.
Add beaten eggs, margarine and flavoring.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: go further brownies
directions: Melt shortening and chocolate together in a 2 quart saucepan. Remove from heat.
Stir in the sugar and vanilla.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder into the chocolate mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add the nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 X 13 inch pan.
Cool and cover with fudge frosting.

title: crescent chicken delight
directions: Mix soup and milk together and heat almost to a boil.
On long end of each crescent roll triangle, put a teaspoon of chicken and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll crescent roll the way up from the end with the meat to the narrow end.
Place rolls in a baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese over all the rolls.
Pour soup mixture over all the rolls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my favorite carrot cake(from the kitchen of sandi brinson)
directions: Sift together 3 times, first 5 ingredients.
In a bowl, beat with mixer on high speed for 5 minutes, Crisco oil and sugar. Reduce mixer to medium speed and blend in, one at a time, eggs and vanilla.
With mixer on low speed, gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Add pineapple and grated carrots.
Mix well and then fold in pecans and dates.
Pour batter into a large 10-inch Bundt or tube pan that has been well greased and floured.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan and then remove.
Place under airtight cake container or tightly wrap in foil.
Store overnight before slicing.

title: scrumptious croutons
directions: Take the
loaf of bread and set slices out to dry.
Cut into cubes. Combine the melted stick of margarine with the Italian dressing.
Mix until it does not separate.
Pour over bread and stir.
Bake a single layer of croutons on a cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes or until they start to get golden brown around the edges. Stir croutons a couple of times while baking.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: In a heavy soup pot saute the bacon until crisp and add the onions, celery and oil. Saute for 5 minutes and then add the flour.
Turn the heat down on low and cook the now formed roux for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat the chicken broth and whisk into the cooked roux.
Season with basil and add the potatoes and cream. Simmer for 30 minutes and add the sour cream and parsley.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Garnish with cheddar cheese when ready to serve.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks in large bowl until light colored.
Add to yolks the sugar and beat until sugar dissolves.
Add 100 proof slowly to egg yellows.
While beating, add whipping cream (without beating). Add whole milk (as much as desired).
Beat egg whites stiff and add a small amount of salt.
Pour egg whites on top of yolk mixture and cut in.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top of each glass as your serve it. Drink and be merry.

title: pork chops parmesan(low-fat)
directions: Combine the cornmeal, Parmesan cheese, black pepper, salt and basil.
Trim the pork chops of all visible fat, pat them dry and dredge in the cornmeal mixture.
Heat a skillet over medium heat. Add the oil.
When the oil is hot, place the chops in the skillet. Reduce the heat to low.
Fry the chops for 10 minutes on each side, then add the onions, garlic and fennel; continue frying for another 10 minutes, turning as necessary to keep from sticking. Makes 4 servings.

title: dreamy cranberry salad(excellent and easy!)
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set.
Whip the cranberry sauce, blend in pineapple and fold in gelatin.
Turn into mold; chill until firm.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool and debone.
Place all ingredients, mixed well, in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: dot's broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, butter, eggs and onion.
Spray 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Layer broccoli, then chicken, then soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese, then Ritz cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prime rib
directions: Season prime rib with salt, pepper and garlic.
Completely pack in rock salt, then slow roast, uncovered, in a 325° convection oven for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.

title: beef and mushroom pie
directions: In butter or margarine, light brown rice and vermicelli.
Add ground beef; finely crumble and continue browning.
Stir in hot water, mushrooms, contents of beef flavor packet, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cool slightly; stir in well-beaten eggs.
Fill a 9-inch unbaked pie shell with Rice-A-Roni mixture. Garnish top with slices of bacon.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Parboil squash 5 minutes; drain.
Combine squash, green pepper, onion and rice.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to rice mixture.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Layer in order given and serve at room temperature or slightly chilled.

title: frances' brownies
directions: Cream shortening and margarine combination with granulated sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix together the flour, cocoa and salt; add to the creamed mixture and blend well.
Add the vanilla; blend and add nuts, blending slightly.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: wassail
directions: Stir all together in large kettle. Simmer gently for about 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions 20 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and water gradually.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Toast bread.
Put bread in baking dish.
Ladle in soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: benne brittle
directions: Spread sesame seed (benne) in large baking pan.
Toast in 350° oven until lightly brown 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Cut in shortening as for pastry. Add water to egg and combine with flour mixture.
Roll out very thin on floured pastry board or table.
Cut into 2 inch squares and add to homemade chicken or beef soup.
Cook until done, about 20 or more minutes.

title: cranberry-pumpkin bread
directions: Combine the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin; mix well.
Combine flour, spice, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Make well in center.
Pour pumpkin mixture into well; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries.
Spoon the batter into 2 greased and floured (8 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/2-inch) aluminum loaf pans.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.
Place fruit in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle oat mixture over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until fruit is tender, about 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or light cream.

title: golden macaroni ring
directions: Pour into well-greased ring mold; set in pan of water (1-inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until set.
Unmold on hot platter; fill center with creamed seafood, chicken, ham or vegetable.
Makes 8 plentiful servings.

title: brown sugar macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and beat to make egg whites dry.
Add brown sugar and beat until well blended. Fold in pecans and drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 200° for 2 hours.
Check after 1 1/2 hours.
They should be colored, but not brown.
Store in airtight container.

title: river bottom pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Mix other in by hand. Add lemon juice last.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm. This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper the pork chops.
Brown lightly.
Lay in a casserole dish.
Pour rice over pork chops.
Add soup and water mixture; salt and pepper soup to taste.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl and stir.
In another bowl, beat eggs, one at a time, then stir in shortening.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients; stir in one cup milk.
Add flavoring and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350° in a preheated oven.
Cool and ice.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine salad dressing, sugar, vinegar, dill and salt, if desired; mix well.
Add cucumbers and onions; toss. Cover and chill for at least 1 one hour.

title: heart-healthy fat-free molasses cookies
directions: Warm molasses to slightly over lukewarm, not hot.
Stir in soda.
Beat egg and sugar.
Add vanilla and stir into molasses. Stir in flour and spices.
Add raisins, if desired.
Shape into 24 balls.
Arrange well apart on Pam-sprayed cookie sheets.
Flatten with moist fork.
Watch closely as they bake, they burn easily. Bake in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes. Store airtight. Best after at least 24 hours of mellowing. Yields 24.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into half baked pie shells* (9-inch).
Cook at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: amaretto
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil; simmer until syrupy.
Let cool.
Add the extract, vodka and brandy.
Stir well.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: ham salad
directions: Combine ham, pineapple, celery and olives.
Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Lightly stir into ham mixture. Chill in refrigerator 1 hour or more. Stir in nuts and serve on lettuce.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine rice and 4 cups of water (1 teaspoon salt, optional) in a large pan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
While rice is cooking, lightly brown each side of pork chops and set aside (about 2 minutes on medium heat for each side).
Combine gravy mix, onion soup mix and 3 cups water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it thickens, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over rice; mix well.
Grease a large casserole dish (lightly with Pam). Layer with rice and single row of pork chops.
Repeat procedure.

title: crown of gold meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, egg yolks, salt, mustard, onions, ketchup and horseradish (optional) well; place in a 9-inch casserole or wide tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and mustard.
Spread over meat loaf; return to oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice onion.
Place into pan.
Spread mushroom soup on top of potatoes. Put pork chops on top.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: herbed walnut rice
directions: Cook onion, carrot, walnut, marjoram, thyme and rosemary in butter.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender and crisp.
Stir in rice and parsley; heat thoroughly. Serves 6.

title: good chicken
directions: Combine ingredients. Pour over chicken breasts and marinate overnight. Drain thoroughly and roll in 1 3/4 cups of bread crumbs. Grease a pan well. Put in chicken. Spoon over it 1/4 cup butter and 1/2 cup shortening (sometimes I use a little less). Put foil over all loosely for 45 minutes at 350°. Then put small amount of water in pan and bake another 20 minutes or until tender. (If you want the chicken more crisp or browner on the outside, put under broiler a few minutes.) Serve on warm platter surrounded with fresh parsley and tiny red crab apples. BEAUTIFUL! GOOD! EASY!

title: spinach stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix together the souffle, lemon pepper, garlic powder and salt. Remove mushroom stems and dip in melted butter; chop stems finely. Add minced onion and saute in 3 tablespoons of butter until soft. Mix with spinach mixture.
Fill mushroom caps until slightly rounded.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° until filling is set and golden (12 to 15 minutes).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Chop canned meat in bite size pieces. Mix in other ingredients.
Combine with salad dressing (Miracle Whip).
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix up flour, baking powder, oil and milk.
Make a dough; put it on the inside of a big bread pan.
Grease the pan first.
Now put cinnamon on top of dough.
Put a layer of sugar.
Put apples on top of sugar and cinnamon.
Put more sugar and cinnamon on top of apples.
Put more cinnamon and sugar on top.
Put a crisscross on top of dough.
Put sugar and cinnamon on top of crust.
Bake in oven about 1 hour.
Eat hot with milk.

title: dump pie
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Stir together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture into melted margarine.
Do not stir.

title: dill potato salad
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling, salted water to cover 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain and let cool to touch.
Leaving skins on, cut potatoes into eighths.
Place in large bowl. Combine mayonnaise and next 7 ingredients; add to potatoes, tossing gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put all in blender and mix well.
For regular oven, bake in greased casserole for 1 hour until set.

title: sangria
directions: Mix all ingredients except club soda and let sit 1 hour.
Add club soda just before serving.
You can also add 4 to 5 strawberries if desired.
The Sangria looks beautiful served in a glass pitcher.

title: sausage bake
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until it begins to brown, stirring to break up large pieces.
Add onion and celery; saute until tender.
Remove sausage and vegetables with a slotted spoon to a well-greased large flat baking pan.
Top with spaghetti. Combine soup and milk; add eggs and cheese.
Pour mixture evenly over spaghetti.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle evenly over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until crumbs are crisp and toasted.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage 3 to 5 minutes.
Peel leaves and set aside. Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Add onion, green pepper and seasonings; simmer 5 minutes.
Mix rice in with hamburger.
Put mixture into separated cabbage leaves.
Roll up leaves and place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour tomato soup over and cabbage water over top of cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Do not use paper liners.
Grease muffin tins well. Bake at 400°.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients to make a marinade in a large container with a lid.
Finely chop garlic cloves and add to marinade.
Stir marinade.
Add chicken wings to marinade; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Put aluminum foil in pan.
Spray with Pam.
Put chicken wings in pan and sprinkle with lemon pepper. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix
water, sugar, salt, salad oil, vinegar and paprika well until
sugar
dissolves.
In bowl mix all vegetables and pour mixture
over.
Let
stand	in covered dish overnight in refrigerator.
Drain 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: becky's homemade salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients and boil 3 hours.
Seal in hot jars.

title: baked french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Peel potatoes and cut into slices, place in bowl of ice water to crisp. Put on paper towel and pat dry before cooking. Spread out potatoes on a shallow pan. Sprinkle potatoes with oil. Shake pan to spread oil evenly. Bake 30 - 40 minutes, turning frequently, until golden brown. Empty potatoes onto paper towels. Sprinkle with salt and paprika.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Mix milk, margarine, eggs, flour, mustard, salt and pepper in blender, or beat thoroughly.
In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan, layer 2 cups bread cubes, 1 1/2 cups cheese and a sprinkle of chives.
Repeat this layering.
Pour egg mixture over all and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a bowl mix all ingredients.
Bake in a roasting pan for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: You will need 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: copper pennies
directions: Add all ingredients to warm carrots; cover tightly and toss upside down.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rice or barley pilaf
directions: Set kettle of water to boil.
Chop onion and slice mushrooms and saute in oil until tender.

Add barley or rice and saute until lightly browned. Carefully add boiling water and bouillon cubes. Bring to a boil, set heat to low, cover and cook on low for 45 minutes for barley or brown rice, and 20 minutes for white rice.

title: diabetic chunky oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl; stir enough to moisten.
Fill 12 lined muffin cups.
Bake 12 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Pour soups and water into pork drippings without meat.
Cook 1 package Kluski noodles.
Mix sauerkraut with noodles.
Add meat, then liquids.
Rinse soup cans with a little water, adding to mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.

title: hamburger stir-fry
directions: Shape beef into 1 large patty.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in wok over high heat.
Brown for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes each side.
Break meat into chunks and stir-fry for 30 seconds.
Remove and set aside.

title: shrimp lo mein
directions: In a bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
In a second bowl, combine vermicelli and soy sauce. Toss to blend thoroughly.

title: patty dorsey salsa
directions: Grind the first seven ingredients together, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook about 2 hours and seal in pint jars. Makes 25 pints.

title: easy boiled custard
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with plain milk (I use a little more milk).
Beat in instant pudding and vanilla until it begins to thicken.
Chill.

title: peanut butter apple cookies
directions: 1. Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: kay's easy chili
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion.
Drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients, bring to a boil.
Then reduce heat to simmer, let simmer 30 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spinach and mushroom pasta
directions: Get a pan hot.
Add whole butter; fizzle in.
Add chopped onion immediately.
Saute awhile, the longer the better, without burning.
Add mushrooms.
Cook awhile longer.
Add more butter, then add cleaned spinach.
Cook until spinach swelling goes down, then add heavy cream.
Cook until looks semi-thick.
Add nutmeg, egg yolk, Parmesan cheese and chicken stock.
Season with pepper and a tab of salt.
Serve on your favorite pasta.
Linguini works well.

title: broccoli and cheese dish
directions: Mix all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda together well.
Add undrained fruit cocktail and eggs. Pour into greased and floured pan and sprinkle with brown sugar and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. While still baking mix together topping.

title: fruit strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray cookie sheet with nonstick spray. In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except phyllo sheets. Spread mixture on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until fruit is tender.
Cool completely.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Layer three phyllo sheets on top of one another.
Spoon one-half mixture along the edge of the phyllo. Roll phyllo jelly roll fashion and place on cookie sheet prepared with nonstick spray.
Spray strudel with spray to prevent drying. Score top of strudel with 7 diagonal cuts.
Do not cut all the way through.
Repeat process for second strudel.
Bake for about 10 minutes.
Yields 2 strudels, 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie with topping
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: holmes barbecue sauce
directions: Cut up the celery and onions. Cut lemons in half.
Squeeze the juice but throw in the rind, too.
Add all the other ingredients in a big pot.
Bring to a fast boil.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Strain out and it is ready to go on your ribs or chicken.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease three 9-inch loaf pans.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in sugar, oil, water and pumpkin; add in flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in dates and peanuts.
Pour 1/3 batter into each loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until bread pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool on wire rack
for 10 minutes.
Yields 3 loaves, 18 servings.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes and mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers, mixed with 1 cup melted butter.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: banana pound cake
directions: Mix shortening, margarine and sugar well.
Add eggs individually and mix well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and add with milk and vanilla. Fold in bananas and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes at 325° in a tube pan.

title: frozen fruit cake
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Try other candied fruits, if desired.

title: enchiladas
directions: Place enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and small amount of water in saucepan to heat.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Add black olives, salt and pepper to taste.
Soften tortillas in small amount of hot oil in another skillet.
Place a spoonful of ground beef mixture in each tortilla.
Add a spoonful of cheese. Roll up and place in baking dish.
Pour enchilada sauce over all. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice together.
Add Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and strawberries.
Combine until smooth and put into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
These can be frozen.

title: cherry or peach pudding(or use blueberries)
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add 1 egg and mix well. Add baking powder, flour and milk.
Mix well.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in milk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Pour in pie crust.
Top with whipped topping or sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Cool in refrigerator for about 2 to 3 hours.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground round and onions.	Add chili sauce, tomato sauce, salt,
pepper,
chili
powder
and catsup. Cook desired length of time.
Several hours makes it delicious!

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and flour all at once (containing salt).
Beat until smooth.
Bake in preheated oven (350°) for 1 hour or until done in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Nuts may be added in bottom of greased and floured pan and on top (pecans or nuts of your choice).
No peeping under any conditions as this cake will fall.

title: avocados stuffed with shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp; place in large bowl and sprinkle with fresh lemon juice.
Add next 7 ingredients, mixing well. Chill.
Fill avocado halves with shrimp mixture.

title: low calorie potato salad
directions: Place cooked potatoes in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Toss to combine.
Chill and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chinese broccoli with oyster sauce
directions: Bring 1/2 pot of water to a boil. Add a dash of salt.
Place the Chinese broccoli in the water and cook for 2 minutes. Remove and drain.
Place on a serving platter and sprinkle with oyster sauce and 1 tablespoon corn oil.
Remove and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well with mixer.
Combine pudding and milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crush Oreos in blender.
Alternate pudding mixture with Oreo mixture to desired number of layers.
Refrigerate.

title: onion-roasted potatoes and chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until everything is evenly coated.
Empty all into shallow baking or roasting pan. Discard bag.
Bake, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are golden brown and tender.
Garnish with fresh, chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into florets. Add onions; set aside. Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli and onion. Refrigerate. (Can be put in plastic Ziploc bag or bowl with lid.)
When ready to serve, add bacon and cheese. Also good leftover.

title: cheesy cocktail swirls
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, onion and crumbled bacon. Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spread about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on each rectangle.
Starting at long side, roll up and seal.
Cut each roll into 8 pieces.
Place pieces cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Lightly sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 32 pieces.

title: wiener creole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in margarine until soft (about 5 minutes) over low heat.
Add tomato sauce, water, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Stir well.
Add franks; let simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add vegetable oil and add water, yogurt and juice.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 6 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed. Pour into 10-cup Bundt pan coated with cooking oil.
Bake until stick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and drizzle with lemon glaze or confectioners sugar.
Enjoy!!

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Mix all together.
Spread mayonnaise on 1 slice of bread; add vegetable mix on this.
Slice sandwich into thirds.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom and sides of pie plate.
Pour in pizza sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Heat oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly the beef, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, salt and pepper, Worcestershire sauce, egg and milk. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars, Crisco, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix well into creamed mixture.
Fold in oats and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken in cream sauce
directions: Wash and season chicken breasts with garlic, salt and pepper. Heat pan.
Then add olive oil.
Add chicken breasts.
Brown on both sides for about 3 minutes each side.

title: five can chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in a large casserole.
Do not dilute soups.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
The last 10 minutes, top with crushed potato chips or, if desired, more chow mein noodles.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Combine margarine and milk; warm in pan to melt margarine. Beat well each item when added to mix.
Beat well 4 eggs, sugar, vanilla and sifted flour.
Fold in slowly, milk and margarine mixture; beat well.
Add baking powder; beat well.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 36 cupcakes, 1 (3 layer) cake or 1 tube pan cake.
Bake at 350°.
Cupcakes and layer cake bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Tube pan bake for 1 hour.

title: watergate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ingredients; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack to cool. Frost when cooled.

title: microwave banana cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine, stirring sugar in gradually. Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and stir into sugar mixture.
Mix bananas into sugar mixture.

title: ellen's scalloped corn
directions: Mix egg, milk, 2/3 cup crumbs, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in corn, onion and pimiento.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Toss melted butter with remaining crumbs; sprinkle atop corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana crunch cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in eggs and banana.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Pour in pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl as listed and mix thoroughly with electric mixer (approximately 2 minutes).
Then pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes on cake rack until loosened.
Remove from the pan and shake on powdered sugar while warm.
Can be frozen whole or sliced and placed in sandwich bags. Keeps well for several months.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch crust and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze. Serve frozen.

title: surprise cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl, except rhubarb; beat well.
Fold in rhubarb; pour in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Over top of batter, sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 cup brown sugar to cover batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut all biscuits into fourths.
Place 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in paper sack.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time; shake to coat well.
Arrange sugar coated biscuit pieces in a well-greased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Place 3/4 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and margarine in pan; bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn upside-down and remove from pan immediately.
Pick pieces off with toothpick or fingers. Excellent with coffee.

title: minnesota wild rice and ham casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Spread in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Layer on rice.
Then sprinkle ham and cover with cheese.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Spread over casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden in color.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Mix 1 box of Jell-) with 1 cup boiling water.
Pour 1/2 cup in a bowl.
Add 2 tablespoons cold water and 1/3 cup sour cream.
Mix well. Strain in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Gel for 50 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to remaining Jell-O.
Pour over first layer.
Gel for 50 minutes.
Repeat with remaining boxes of Jell-O.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.	Refrigerate.
Excellent on tossed, spinach and cabbage salads.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs all together well in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients (except apples, nuts and raisins) and stir until mixed.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Bake in 3 layers (9-inch pan) at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak and gravy
directions: Mix salt, pepper and paprika with flour.
Dip steak pieces in seasoned flour, then in egg and water beaten together.
Dip again in flour.
Brown on both sides in hot fat.
Cover; cook slowly 20 or 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw to freeze
directions: Shred cabbage, carrots and green pepper and mix.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Let cool.

title: ground beef in sour cream casserole
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender but not brown.
Place noodles in layer over meat. Combine tomato juice, salt, celery salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; pour over noodles.
Bring to boiling; cover and simmer over low heat 20 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Cover and continue cooking 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream and mushrooms.
Heat just to boiling.
Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except last 2.
Put into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spring salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given, beginning with the green peas.
Let set 24 hours before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fry 1 pound bacon crisp.
Brown 2 onions in bacon drippings. Clean and break up 1 head broccoli and put in pot.
Use approximately 2 cups of water.
Steam until almost done.
Add 3 cans of soup.
Mix altogether.
Cut up 1 pound Velveeta cheese and add to soup.
Crumble bacon and add onions.
Cook for 20 minutes on low.
Add more mushroom soup or cheese, as desired.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Place mixture into a square cake pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: dijon-glazed chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well.
Place chicken in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch dish coated with cooking spray. Brush glaze mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is done.
Uncover and broil chicken 4 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.
Yield: 4 servings (about 160 calories per serving and 2.1 fat grams).

title: amanda's chex mix
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine. After melted, add rest of ingredients to saucepan. Add melted mix to large bowl. Stir with spoon until all pieces have sauce on them.

title: no cook cherry pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir thoroughly until mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Turn mixture into baked crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator (do not freeze).
Before serving, garnish top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Melt butter and mix with cookies (all but 1 cup).
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread ice cream over cookies. Freeze until firm.
Spread hot fudge and sprinkle with nuts.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved cookies.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and egg whites separately.
Then combine both and add baking soda, rum and sugar.
Beat until stiff (5 minutes). Add half and half and rye whiskey.
Stir to blend.
Do not use a mixer.
Chill and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients in bowl; add to shortening.
Mix with egg, milk, cheese and parsley.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: cranberry raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins until puffy.
Cut cranberries in half and wash in colander to remove seeds.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water and add salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add boiling water and cook 10 minutes longer.
Add raisins and cranberries.
Bake in unbaked pie shell. Make a lattice work top with pastry strips.
Bake about 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, salt and evaporated milk, mixing until creamy.
Turn mixture into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar. Stir in pumpkin.
Add lemon juice.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan or line with wax paper.
Add batter and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: saucy bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar
together
until
fluffy.
Add applesauce and beat good.
Add dry ingredients and beat good. Then vanilla.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm,
ice with
sugar, milk and vanilla frosting.

title: salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together with the water, then pour over the meat.
It mixes better this way.
Mix well and shape into rolls.
Wrap in foil (shiny side out).
Refrigerate for 24 hours. Place in pan with water to cover rolls and boil for 1 hour.
When done, can eat or be frozen.

title: white spaghetti
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and soak.
Cook noodles; drain and reserve 1 cup of water to mix with oil mix.
Toss noodles in oil mix, adding salt and Parmesan cheese to taste. Squeeze 1 can of tomatoes into spaghetti and stir.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Mix soup with 1/2 can of water.
Put 1/2 stuffing mix in crock-pot.
Pour half of the soup mixture over this.
Season the chops and place all of them on top of stuffing.
Pour rest of the soup mixture over the meat and top with rest of stuffing.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery or celery salt, bell pepper, green onions and white onions.
Add beans, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Add barbecue sauce, ketchup, syrup and hot sauce to taste.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and put aside to cool. Add vanilla. Cream together sugars, shortening and eggs. Add dry ingredients and beat well. Stir in oatmeal. Bake at 350° until done.

title: holiday mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
When done, mash hot potatoes in a large bowl until smooth.
Add cream cheese in small pieces, then oleo.
Beat until completely mixed.
Mix in sour cream.
Add eggs and onion to milk, then mix into potatoes.
Add salt and beat until light and fluffy.
Place in a large, well-greased, square or oblong casserole dish.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.

title: five can mexican casserole
directions: Brown and chop up lean ground beef in skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together in large deep pan or skillet taco sauce, enchilada sauce, green chilies, pinto beans and mushroom soup.
Add ground beef.
Simmer low 15 minutes.
Layer bottom of 8 x 13-inch casserole (3-quart) with thin layer of crushed Doritos.
Add half of mixture from skillet and cover with Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Crush graham crackers; melt butter and put the two ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan with some sugar.
Spread over entire pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious lemon cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients for two minutes at medium speed.
Roll into small balls, dipping hands into ice water at the onset of the rolling of each ball.
Roll each ball in powdered sugar and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for approximately eight minutes.
Produces 3 dozen cookies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a mixer until well blended. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate sauce(for cake or ice cream)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Boil in a saucepan for 1 minute.
Serve hot.
Great on cake or ice cream.

title: dietetic applesauce raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until water is almost gone.
Beat the oil, eggs and applesauce, then add the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine butter, garlic, ground beef, salt, pepper and sugar in a skillet.
Saute until beef is done. Add Prego and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions together.
Lightly grease a casserole dish and layer ingredients like this:
1/3 macaroni, 1/3 onion mixture and 1/3 meat sauce.
Repeat layers 2 more times. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue marinate(brisket barbecue entertaining)
directions: Marinate brisket in sauce overnight.
Place whole brisket over hot coals to sear and brown fat.
Place brisket and sauce in foil pan.
Cover and cook over coals, approximately 4 hours (using a meat thermometer, 170° for medium).
Slice and serve.
Serves 16. I personally prefer the recipe without the chili sauce.
Perfect for large barbecues.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press mixture across bottom and sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb meringue bars
directions: Cream butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove and cover with filling.
Top with meringue and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Mix cream cheese with sugar until sugar is dissolved.
In bowl, mix Dream Whip as directed on package or use Cool Whip. Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Line bottom and sides of pie shells with sliced bananas.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with blueberry pie filling.
Chill.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: easter eggs
directions: Shape and chill.
Coat with melted chocolate bits.

title: good hot sandwiches(makes 10)
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Scoop a little out of the center of hot dog buns.
Fill with meat-cheese mixture.
Wrap in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: easy hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add well beaten egg, sugar, salt and oil.
Mix well.
Add flour gradually, mixing well.
Pour out on a floured board.
Knead well.
Put into large bowl with a small amount of oil, greasing both sides of the batter.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake in a 425° oven.
When rolls begin to brown, butter tops of rolls and return to oven until well brown.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix together well and put into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry, drain and set aside bacon.
Simmer onions, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard for 20 minutes in bacon grease.
Drain juice off kidney, lima and butter beans.
Add these to crock-pot.
Add pork and beans with juice to crock-pot.
Then add bacon and onion mixture.
Cook in crock-pot all day (4 to 6 hours).

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, salt and flour.
Then add lemon juice and rind.
Add slightly beaten egg yolk and milk.
When well blended, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake in hot oven, 450°, for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 minutes.
Inserted knife will come out clean when done.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix together and chill before serving.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain orange and pineapple.
Combine all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: crock-pot macaroni pie
directions: Mix and place in greased crock-pot.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cook on low for 4 hours.
Check after 3 to 3 1/2 hours as some pots cook faster than others.

title: rice picnic salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and
toss
lightly with a fork. Chill thoroughly.

title: dump salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: uncooked 7 minute icing
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Add the boiling water.
Beat until it has high peaks.
Add any color food coloring you choose.
Spread on cake and set in a cool place for several hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9x13-inch pyrex dish.
Add flour and mix until dissolved.
Add whipping cream and blend well.
Add corn. Add very little salt because butter is already salted.

title: date nut balls
directions: Stir all ingredients together, except coconut.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Let cool enough to handle.
Form into balls; roll in coconut.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix with mixer or blender.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large saucepan, mix sugar, Karo syrup and butter.
Heat until boiling; let boil 3 minutes.
Add pecans to syrup mixture, bringing to a boil again.
Remove from heat and mix in eggs.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate icebox cake
directions: You will need 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.

title: chocolate refresher bars
directions: Sift
flour,
soda and salt.
Combine in large saucepan dates, brown
sugar,
water
and	oleo;
cook
over low heat, stirring constantly	until
dates
soften.
Remove from heat. Stir
in chips.
Blend in eggs and mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice and milk.
Blend thoroughly after each
addition.
Stir in chopped nuts.
