Spread in well-greased 15 x
10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 1/2 cup.
Mix crumbs with butter and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: white sauce
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil in a large saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer until reduced by half. Discard bay leaf. Process wine mixture in a blender until smooth. Scrape down sides. Return mixture to saucepan and whisk in whipping cream. Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, whisking occasionally. Whisk in butter and the remaining ingredients. Makes 3 cups. Delicate in taste. Wonderful over chicken, fish or veal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, beef, onion and sauce together.
Roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: glossy chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch; add chocolate.
Add water.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Spread on cake while frosting is hot for a glossy frosting which remains soft and smooth.
Frosts one 9 x 9-inch square cake.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Drain beans.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.

title: texas cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in the 6 cups water.
Add butter and cheese and stir until butter and cheese are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 11-inch pan in 350° oven until set.

title: sunday spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach.
Layer spinach, mushrooms, onion and frozen peas in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, pepper and curry powder. Top salad with this mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Mix and top with bacon before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pineapple rings
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, Sweet 'N Low, butter, orange juice with pumpkin pie spice, orange peel, pecans and raisins.
Mix well. Drain pineapple slices and place in baking dish.
Mound 1/3 cup of sweet potato mixture on each pineapple top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 10 servings.

title: betty's orange b-day cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and add baking powder.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs, 1 at a time.
Add orange rind.
Add dry ingredients alternately with orange juice, stirring only enough after each addition to blend thoroughly.
Do not beat. Bake 8-inch layers 25 minutes at 375°; cupcakes for 15 minutes at 375°; loaf cake at 350° for 1 hour.
Frost when cool with orange frosting.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and pat together to form crust on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes; do not brown. Combine softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix. Spread on cooled crust.
Chop all veggies fine in any amount you like; mix together and spread on crust, pressing in slightly.
Top with cheese and chill.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Clean and thinly slice mushrooms.
Saute in butter until lightly browned.
Stir in butter and cream and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add vermouth and scallops.
Taste and add salt and pepper as needed.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: joy's taco salad
directions: Beef or chicken can be lightly sauteed with taco seasoning mix for flavor if desired.
Meat, beans and corn should be warm.
All other toppings should be cold.

title: sloppy toms
directions: Coat skillet with Pam; place over medium-high heat.
Add turkey and next 3 ingredients.
Cook until browned, stirring to crumble turkey.
Drain and return turkey mixture to skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: peanut butter balls in chocolate
directions: Mix peanut butter, nuts, cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and coconut.
Melt butter; pour over mixture.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture; place on wax paper.

title: jade green broccoli
directions: Mix together sugar, m.s.g., cornstarch, soy sauce and stock. Set aside.
Heat wok hot and dry.
Add oil, then salt. Reduce heat to medium and add the garlic.
When garlic is golden brown, add the broccoli.
Turn heat up and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add the sherry and cover wok quickly.
Cook, covered, for 2 minutes longer.
Lift cover and add the sugar-m.s.g. mixture while stirring.
When the gravy has thickened, transfer to a serving dish.
Garnish with bacon bits if you like.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Melt and cook 5 minutes, boiling.
Add several drops food coloring and 1 teaspoon cinnamon oil.
Pour over popcorn and stir well.
Put on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pastry shells
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon 1 teaspoon filling into each shell.
Bake at 350° for 17 minutes.

title: crunchy ice cream dessert
directions: Slowly brown slivered almonds in 2 tablespoons oleo; drain on paper toweling and salt.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo and add brown sugar while on stove.
Remove from heat and add coconut, Rice Chex and almonds.
Put 1/2 mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice ice cream and place over mixture.
Put other 1/2 of mixture on top of ice cream.
Cover tightly and freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended. Put in 2 greased bread pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 10 minutes.
Beat egg whites until creamy.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue to beat until mixture stands in peaks.
Add chocolate bits, then add vanilla.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Drop by teaspoon on foil.
Turn off oven at once after placing sheets inside.
Do not open oven for 9 hours.

title: dill pickle
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers and place in jars.
Boil water, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over cucumbers.
Place several pieces of dill on top and seal while hot.

title: chili rellenos(yields 4 servings)
directions: Make a slit in each chili and stuff with a piece of cheese. Roll each chili in flour and set aside.
Heat oil in large, deep pan.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.

title: taco soup
directions: Dump above ingredients into large pot and simmer 30 minutes or more.
Use with chips, cheese, and sour cream.

title: confetti dip
directions: Mix eggs, vinegar and sugar in a double boiler.
Mix over medium heat until it becomes like scrambled eggs.
Remove from heat.
Mix in the cream cheese, pepper and onion.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: deviled eggs(club member:  ashley wilson)
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise in half. Slip out yolks; mash with fork. Mix in seasoning and salad dressing. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up slightly.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Brown chicken breasts in skillet.

title: super bowl sunday chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot in order listed.
Stir once. Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 5 to 6 hours).

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat; add onions, peppers, garlic and broth mix.
Saute until onions are translucent.
Combine vegetables with all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber in sour cream
directions: Peel and slice thinly the cucumbers.
Chill well. Combine the remaining ingredients and toss with the cucumbers.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13 ungreased cake pan.	Put ingredients in cake pan as they are listed above.
Spread or sprinkle ingredients evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm or cold, plain, or with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: punch
directions: Any flavor of Hi-C; match with various flavors of sherbet.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Cook
and
drain ground beef.
Mix soup, milk, eggs and spices.
Stir
in
ground beef and cheese.	Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until set.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix cooked noodles together with all vegetables.
Add Italian dressing and Salad Supreme.
Toss and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip whites and add 6 tablespoons sugar (from the 2 2/3 cups) while beating.
Place in refrigerator while mixing rest of cake.
Cream butter, adding gradually remainder of sugar and whipping until light.
Add egg yolks, about two at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and cream alternately. Using low speed of mixer, whip until mixture is as light as possible.
Add vanilla. fold in or whip in the egg whites with mixer till at low speed, only long enough to mix well.
Pour batter into prepared 10-inch or 4-inch tube pan.
(Spray with Baker's Joy or grease and flour.)
Bake as you would an angel food cake, about 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.
This cake is of wonderful texture and can be sliced "as thin as a dime."
It's worth giving a party just to bake it!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Cook in a greased and floured tube pan about an hour and a half or until done at 275°.

title: barbecued pork steak
directions: Melt shortening.
Roll pork in flour and brown.
Place in roaster.
Mix onions, green pepper, catsup, salt, celery seed, brown sugar, lemon juice and mustard with 1 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: texas beans and rice
directions: Saute meat in oil, bell pepper and onion.
Drain off excess oil.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and chili powder.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add raw rice and beans.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir and cook 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Add other ingredients. Put in crock pot and cook on low for 3 hours.

title: chicken with ham and cheese(chicken cordon bleu)
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into round 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar and then add pineapple and maraschino cherries.
Whip heavy whipping cream and fold into the mixture.
Put in a 9-inch square glass pan or dish and freeze. Take out about 1/2 hour before serving.

title: italian wedding soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in small bowl and stir well. Shape mixture into 56 (3/4-inch) meatballs.
Set meatballs aside.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet brown meat, mix the juice from meat with mushroom and onion soup mix.
Mix together with meat, noodles and sauerkraut.
Pour into greased casserole dish; microwave to heat through, or bake for one hour at 350°.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix well all ingredients except Jiffy mix; add it last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° or until brown.
Serves 12.

title: double chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Butter 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 8 x 11-inch baking pan.
Stir milk and chips in 2-quart microwave-safe casserole; add chocolate. Microwave uncovered on High 1 minute.
Stir.
Microwave until chocolate is melted and mixture can be stirred smooth, about 2 minutes longer.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Spread evenly in pan. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Makes about 2 lb. of candy.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook vegetables until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Set aside.
Saute onions in oleo until soft.
Stir in flour and season to taste.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Stir in vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of liquid.
Cook until desired consistency.
Makes 8 to 10 servings, 2 1/2 quarts.

title: ribbon salad
directions: First Layer: strawberry jello, boiling water and strawberries.
Put in refrigerator until set in clear, oblong Pyrex pan. After first layer is set, top with sour cream or cream cheese; this is your second layer.

title: swiss onion spiral bread
directions: In a small skillet, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
On floured surface, roll out bread dough to a 17 x 7-inch rectangle; spread cooked onion evenly over dough.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon atop.
Roll up jelly roll fashion from the long side, pinching edges to seal.
Place loaf, formed into slightly crescent shape, seam side down, on a greased cookie sheet.
Score top of loaf crosswise, making cuts 1/4-inch deep.
Cover; let rise in a warm place 30 to 45 minutes or until almost double.
Brush top of bread with egg; sprinkle with poppy seed or dill seed.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Loaf should sound hollow when tapped.
Serve warm.
To reheat, wrap in foil.
Heat in 400° oven for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: butter nut balls
directions: Cream butter until soft and smooth.
Add sugar gradually, creaming after each addition.
Blend in egg yolks and rind and beat until fluffy.
Add half the flour, then milk and remaining flour.
Knead slightly to blend thoroughly.
Chill 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pecan bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: mother ripp's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine in top of double boiler.
Drop in chocolate and melt.
Gradually add sugar, 4 tablespoons at a time.
Add salt. Gradually add milk.
The water in the double boiler must be kept boiling.
Lastly, add vanilla.
Cook until desired thickness, about 1 hour.
Stir often.
Store in refrigerator.
Can be reheated.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches with juice in pan.
Sprinkle jello and cake mix over peaches.
Pour the water over all.
Place butter on top. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in jar.
Use as you would instant coffee, but have Russian Tea instead.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: In large heavy pan, brown meat in shortening; pour off fat. Add gravy, 1 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook 1 hour more or until tender. Stir.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: anna's flat bread
directions: Mix the oatmeal, flour, cereal, margarine and sugar as for pastry.
Add the water and soda mixture. Blend well.
Refrigerate to cool.
Roll thin and bake to golden brown in a 350° oven. Can use a Spam can to cut or cut with a knife to size desired before baking.

title: curried lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed.
Drain reserving liquid as part of the 1/2 cup water to the soup.
Combine onion, red pepper, soup and water in a saucepan.
Heat through.
Remove from heat.
Blend sour cream and curry powder into soup mixture.
Stir in lima beans.
Put mixture into a 6-cup casserole.
Combine bread crumbs with melted butter.
Stir in bacon crumbles.
Sprinkle over lima mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 minutes until
crumb topping is browned.

title: sausage and creamed potatoes
directions: Cut sausage into 2-inch pieces.
In a large pot, brown sausage with chopped onion.
Add water to cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add cut potatoes and seasoning to meat.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done (about 20 minutes).
Blend flour into milk, add to sausage and potatoes and cook until thickened.

title: grandmother thrasher's pineapple and chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 layer pans following package directions, substituting pineapple juice drained from pineapple for water. Bake and cool.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well and bake at 425° until the bread springs back to touch.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until cheese is soft, butter is melted and mixture is well blended.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir until well-combined.
Add your choice of food coloring and flavoring.
If desired, divide batch to make 2 or 3 colors.

title: chocolate chunk oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: granny's banana pudding
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk, mixing at medium speed until well blended.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix; beat at low speed 1 minute.
Layer 1/3 of pudding mix, half of wafers and half of bananas in 1 1/2-quart serving bowl; repeat layers.
Top with remaining pudding.
Cover and chill.
Garnish with additional banana slices and wafers.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Prepare eggplant by peeling and cutting the top from the eggplant. Rinse well; cut in little squares. Place in pot and add a little water and about 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to boil; turn heat down to medium. Pour off excess water after eggplant is done. Use potato masher to mash up eggplant.

Turn stove eye off and add the butter. Grate cheese in food processor and the package of saltine crackers after the cheese. Pour over into boiler and stir. In a small bowl, break eggs; beat slightly. Pour over into boiler. Also add 1 1/2 cup milk. Sprinkle a little pepper. Mash all ingredients with potato masher. Pour over in casserole dish and place in oven. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas cake from australia
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients together, except for the baking powder. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Fold in preserves and pineapple.
Last, add dates, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Bake in 4 layers at 350° for 30 minutes.
May take a little longer.
When cold, put together with filling.

title: tamale pie casserole
directions: Fry onions and garlic slowly in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown quickly.
Add green pepper, then remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a large (3-quart),
greased casserole or baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Bake at 250° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until firm.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar.
Add oil and vanilla and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add loosely packed grated zucchini.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into 8 x 4-inch greased and floured loaf pan or 3 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. (Bake 45 minutes for small loaves.)
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Serve plain or with cream cheese.

title: baked chicken and lentils
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine dry ingredients and add hot water.
Stir gently to mix.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus, cheese and pimento in layers in casserole. Spread mushroom soup evenly over this and top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Put in a crock-pot first 4 ingredients on medium heat until cheese melts.
Then turn down to low heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Combine cookies and butter and pat on bottom of spring-form pan.
Beat cream cheese; add milk.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
In plastic baggies, toss chips in flour, then add to cheese mixture.
Pour cheese mixture on top of crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Saute
onions
and green peppers in margarine in medium skillet
until
tender.
Stir
in
chicken, 1 cup cheese, sour cream,
hot
sauce
and
pepper.
Roll
each biscuit to 1/4 to 1/8-inch
thickness.
Spread
each biscuit with about 2 tablespoons
chicken mixture.
Roll up biscuits jelly roll fashion, pinching
edge to seal.
Place rolls in a lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: the "best" brisket
directions: Remove excess fat from the brisket, then score across meat at a diagonal with sharp knife.
Place in roaster.
Mix together cocktail sauce, dry soup mix and Coke.
Pour over brisket.
Cover and bake 3 to 4 hours at 300° to 325° until fork-tender.
Remove brisket from juices and cool.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Put juices into container and refrigerate.
Next day, slice beef. Remove fat from top of juices and pour over slices.
Heat in microwave.

title: dessert squares
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until white.
Slowly beat in sugar and baking powder.
Continue beating for 5 minutes until light and lemon-colored.
Mix in nuts.
Generously butter an 8-inch square baking pan.
Pour into pan.
Smooth top evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until top feels dry.
Cool.
There will be a dry shell on top.
Press it down, making the top look crumbly.
Cut into squares.
Top with berries or fruit if desired.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cut fish into 2-inch squares.
In large saucepan, bring 2 cups water to boiling.
Add potatoes and carrot.
Simmer 5 minutes. Stir in fish and salt.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes.

title: pear jam
directions: Cut pears in small pieces or grind through food grinder with sugar.
Boil pears and sugar until thick and clear, then add cherries cut in small pieces, using juice to heat through and seal.
I also make it by using oranges and lemons.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Top each with ham and cheese and roll up and secure with toothpick.
Makes sauce from remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 minutes, uncovered for 20 minutes more. Serves 4.
Six grams fat.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Set cheese out until soft.
Add confectioners sugar and beat well.
Fold in peanut butter and beat with mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip. Place in graham cracker crust.
Chill for several hours in refrigerator or freezer and set in refrigerator before serving.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Cook rice the way you usually would.
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg curry
directions: For 4 people.
Heat the butter and fry the chopped onions slowly.
Add all the spices, salt and coconut.
Mix well and fry slowly 2 to 3 minutes.
Then add the sliced tomatoes.
Stir this as you add the yogurt or sour cream.
Let this simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Then cut the warm, hard boiled eggs and add them to the curry.
(Try to keep the yolks and whites together.)
With a spoon, cover the eggs with the curry; put the lid on and allow the curry to simmer for 10 minutes.
Place in a serving dish and serve hot with rice or Rice Pulao.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-cup tube pan.
Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool and glaze.
Mix powdered sugar and milk until smooth; pour over cake.

title: fudge magic
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, melt chocolate morsels in Radarange oven for 2 minutes, turning dish after first minute.
Stir until smooth.
Blend in milk, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts and turn mixture into a buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch container to cool. Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 64 (1-inch) squares.

title: mexican corn strips
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large zip-top, heavy-duty plastic bag.
Set aside.
Coat 1 side of each tortilla with cooking spray.
Cut each into 8 strips.
Place strips in bag; seal bag and shake to coat.
Place strips in a single layer on baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crisp.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 8 servings.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 10-inch quiche pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheeses on bottom of pan.
Add vegetables.
Beat together milk, half and half, eggs, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Place asparagus spears on top in spoke pattern, pressing into egg mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beating in one at a time.
Add soda and molasses mixture, then spices and flour. Chill dough.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Melt Hershey bars; set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs; add melted Hershey bars, buttermilk, flour, soda, salt, Hershey syrup and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add pecans and cherries (cut in small pieces).
Mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix one-half can of onions and cream cheese in potatoes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Form shell with potatoes.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.
Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Place broccoli on potato shell.
Add remainder of onions.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: vegetable medley
directions: In large heavy pan, brown mushrooms and cook zucchini, green pepper and onion with garlic and basil in oil 5 minutes.
Add soup and salt.
Cover; cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Uncover; cook 5 minutes more.
Serve with Parmesan.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: texas cornbread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until light.
Stir in buttermilk and oil. Combine dry ingredients in a separate bowl.
Mix in buttermilk mixture until smooth.
Pour in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly at lowest speed until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes about 4 cups or enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large dish.
Seal with mayonnaise. Top with green onions.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook and brown bacon; add chopped onion and cook slowly until tender.
Set aside.
In a large pot, cook potatoes in just enough water to cover.
Add bacon and onion mixture to cooked potatoes; do not drain water.
Add other ingredients and simmer on low.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, sugar, egg and flavorings. Blend in flour and salt. Divide dough in 1/2; blend food color in half of dough. Shape 1 teaspoon dough from each 1/2 into 4-inch rope (roll back and put on floured board). Press together and twist. Place on ungreased baking sheet; curve top of cookies to form a candy cane.
Bake 9 minutes or until set at light brown. (May mix 1/2 cup crushed peppermint candy and 1/2 granulated sugar.) Immediately sprinkle with candy mixture and remove from sheet.

title: kentucky pecan cake
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar,
oil, applesauce, cinnamon, egg yolks and
hot water in order listed; beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff; fold into batter. Pour mixture into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Invert pan and cool cake completely; remove from
pan.
Sprinkle
top
of
cake
with powdered sugar.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Delicious.

title: easy double-chocolate pudding pie(sugar-free)
directions: In a bowl, mix white chocolate pudding, half of the container of Cool Whip and 3/4 cup of milk until well blended.
Then pour into pie crust. Repeat these same steps with the chocolate pudding. Chill in refrigerator for about 2 hours and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Bake in oblong pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp italian
directions: Cut
each
shrimp in half lengthwise.
In large skillet heat oil
and
butter;
add
onion,
green pepper, mushrooms, garlic, salt
and pepper.
Saute until vegetables are tender. Add shrimp and oregano.
Cook 5 minutes longer; add wine.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, set aside.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating as you go.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Fold in flour and sweet milk alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixed.
Bake in tube pan at 350°, about 1 hour or until done.
Turn out on cake plate to cool.
Leave pan on top.

title: shredded beef sandwiches
directions: Trim fat, cut to fit crock-pot. Combine ingredients (except rolls).
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low 11 to 12 hours until meat is tender.
Remove meat and use two forks to shred. Place on buns.
Strain juices.
Skim off fat.
Serve in bowls for dipping.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Let mixture stand one hour at room temperature.
Cream shortening with the sugars until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon into the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add orange juice, bananas, pineapple, strawberries and mandarin oranges.
Stir until juice is dissolved.
Add soda.

title: chicken julia
directions: Day before, wrap each breast with 1 slice of bacon.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with shredded dried beef.
Arrange chicken on top.
In bowl, mix sour cream and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight (or at least 8 hours).
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients including juice into large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice or 1/2 cup grape juice or fruit punch.
Place in refrigerator for a few hours.
Great summer treat.

title: cajun black-eyed peas
directions: Place peas in a large Dutch oven; add water to depth of 2-inches above peas. Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight. Drain peas and return to Dutch oven. Add 8 cups water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add bacon and next 12 ingredients; return to a boil. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 30 minutes or until peas are tender. Add sausage, ham and tomatoes; return to boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Yields 14 cups.

title: fresh strawberry pudding
directions: In large bowl, layer vanilla wafers and sliced strawberries until bowl is full.
Mix rest of ingredients in another bowl until well blended.
Pour over wafers and strawberries.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Refrigerate.
Best if sets overnight.

title: easy rice dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into
a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for 1 hour and uncover for the last 1/2 hour.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Grease 2 (1 pound) coffee cans with lids, too.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water in a large bowl.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons sugar, evaporated milk, salt and salad oil.
With mixer on low, beat in 3 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing well.
Beat in 1 more cup flour with heavy spoon (4 1/2 cups in all).
Add raisins, if desired.

title: crab and corn a la creme
directions: In blazer of chafing dish or in a saucepan over direct heat, melt butter.
Stir in corn, crabmeat, salt, pepper, paprika, mustard, lemon rind, Worcestershire and cream.
Cook, stirring, until hot.
Meanwhile, toast bread.
Cut into triangles.
On it serve corn mixture sprinkled with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mock mince pie
directions: Add a few chopped apples to each pie.
This makes 4 pies.

title: sheri's frozen peach pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese.
Add pureed peaches, whipped cream, lemon juice, milk, almond extract and food coloring.
Pour into crusts and freeze at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer about 15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy au gratin potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
In 1-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook onions until tender. Stir in soup and cream cheese cubes.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and hot.
In casserole, alternately layer frozen potatoes and hot cream sauce, ending with a sauce layer.
Cover and bake 45 minutes until sauce is bubbly and potatoes are tender. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 2 round cake pans and set aside to cool.
Make pudding and set in refrigerator to get cold.
Cut 1 layer of cake in small chunks, put in large bowl.
Spread half of pudding on top, then half of pineapple, then 1 box of strawberries.
Slice 1 banana on top. Cover completely with half of Cool Whip.
Repeat each layer with remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Cook sugar, flour, salt, juice and eggs until thick.
Cool. Cook acini de pepe for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Add rest of ingredients.
Set overnight.

title: coconut joe pound cake
directions: Mix each ingredient slowly, mixing well between ingredients. Put in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the cooking oil and sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs and vanilla.
Measure and sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture.
Stir in chopped fresh apples and nuts and combine thoroughly with other ingredients. Pour into tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: preachers casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook a few minutes.
Put aside 1/3 of the noodles and mix the rest with the other ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole pan.
Top with noodles that have been saved.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven baked jambalaya
directions: Combine all ingredients into a large roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: puffed rice balls
directions: Cook molasses, sugar and water to a soft ball.
Add butter. Cook, stirring constantly, until a few drops become hard in cold water.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Press into bottom of greased, 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) about 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
With spoon, gradually blend in flour.
Mix in nuts.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cookies should be a creamy color.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Store in tightly covered container.
Cookies will be a rounded shape with a flat bottom.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt fat in a saucepan.
Add potatoes, onion and pimento. Simmer until onion begins to brown, then sprinkle with minced parsley.
Add hot stock or water.
Stir in paprika.
Season with salt.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon sour cream and cook 3 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: micro summer squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into 1-inch pieces and combine with onion in a greased 6-cup shallow, microwave casserole dish, covered with plastic wrap.
Microwave on full power for 7 minutes.
Drain all liquid from dish and save it for soup or sauce.
Beat eggs in a medium size bowl with
a wire whip until foamy.
Stir in cheese, salt, basil and pepper until well blended.
Pour over squash in casserole, stirring to mix well. Cover casserole with a paper towel.
Microwave at Medium power 5 minutes.
Remove the paper towel.
Microwave 3 minutes longer or until egg mixture is set. Before serving, garnish with parsley.
Very good.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in greased casserole dish (covered) at 350°.
Remove cover and bake 20 minutes longer until brown. Serves 10.

title: chicken chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat to warm for approximately 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bran muffins
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with nonfat cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.

title: ranch dressing
directions: If only a small amount is made, I omit the Accent.
Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: raspberry fig preserves
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 7 minutes.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: crunchy orange gelatin salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Follow directions for making Jell-O using the pineapple juice for some of the liquid.
Pour prepared Jell-O in a 9 x 13-inch dish and set aside to cool.
Grate carrots very fine.
Add carrots and pineapple to cooled Jell-O and refrigerate.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chili
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Place in large pot, add cumin seed, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, wine and some salt and pepper.
Simmer all for 45 minutes.
Add red kidney beans and simmer 15 minutes more.

title: boneless chicken breasts
directions: Line
bottom
of pan with dried beef; wrap each chicken breast in
one
slice
of bacon.	Place on top of dried beef. Mix
sour cream
to
each
can
of
mushroom soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 2	hours
at
300°, then turn up to 350° for 1 more hour. Breasts that are thin use less cooking time.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small casserole dish, combine corn muffin mix, cream-style and whole kernel corn.
Stir together well.
Cut stick of butter up into small pieces and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Bake at 400° approximately 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: date cookies - candy
directions: Mix egg with sugar and margarine.
Add dates.
Put in an electric skillet; cook 5 minutes at 300° until thick paste.
Let cool; add vanilla flavor, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Then roll in small balls.
Then roll in coconut.

title: puppy chow
directions: In microwave, melt chips, margarine and peanut butter on High for 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir and heat again for one minute.
In large bowl, pour chocolate over Crispix; stir carefully.
Put confectioners sugar in large grocery sack.
Pour chocolate Crispix into sack and shake until coated.

title: julie's cookies
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients. Add the flour, soda, salt, oil and vanilla to the sugar mixture. Add the remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. This recipe makes a lot and keeps well.

title: quick and dirty italian cream cake
directions: Cut cookies lengthwise.
Line bottom of 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cook vanilla pudding; after thickens, add rum extract.
Stir.
Pour hot over cookies.
Do a second layer of cookies.
Pour hot chocolate pudding on top.
Put cherries on pudding.
Refrigerate.
When cool, cover top with Cool Whip and sprinkle on pecans.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend butter and sugar until creamy. Add eggs and beat.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Add Seven-Up, lemon and vanilla flavoring.
Cook for 1 hour or until cake springs back when touched.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, water and margarine until melted.
Add beaten eggs, flour, brown sugar and white sugar, vanilla and cinnamon. Mix until moist.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°. Remove from pan and cool.
Slice and serve with a thin coating of margarine, if desired.

title: broiled artichoke rounds
directions: Drain artichokes and coarsely chop.
Stir in mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Mound cheese mixture on muffin halves and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place muffin halves on cookie sheet and broil until lightly browned.
Yields:
12 rounds.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost.

title: taos chicken
directions: Roll chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in pan and brown chicken.
Push to side.
Now saute onion.
Add rest of ingredients (except rice).
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 35 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Combine yogurt and Cool Whip in bowl.
Spoon into pie crusts to top edge of shell.
Cover with original plastic covering.
Put pies in refrigerator until filling is firm.
Light, fluffy and very tasty.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water; set aside.
Mix cake mix with eggs, oil and extract, then add Jell-O mixture.
Bake as directed on cake mix box.
When taken out of the oven, poke holes in cake with a toothpick.
Pour hot glaze over the top.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar; add eggs, baking soda and sour cream. Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spray 9 x 3-inch pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick is dry.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and vanilla until fluffy. Gradually add sugar.

title: grape salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugars & vanilla; toss in pecans and grapes.

title: ultimate onion
directions: Mix cornstarch, flour and seasonings until well blended.
Add beer and mix well.
Cut about 3/4-inch off top of onions and peel. Cut into onion 12 to 16 vertical wedges, but do not cut through bottom (root end).
Remove about 1-inch of "petals" from center of onion.
Dip cut onion in seasoned flour and remove excess by shaking.
Dip in batter and remove excess by gently shaking. Separate "petals" to coat thoroughly with batter.
Mix batter after standing to blend ingredients.

title: chicken sauce for hot biscuits
directions: Boil chicken, onions, salt, pepper, carrots and bouillon until chicken falls apart and vegetables are done (approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
May have to add water when boiling.
Cool.
Finely dice chicken.
Using as much stock as necessary and all vegetables, put in bowl and add soup.
Mix and stir to right consistency.
Pour over hot biscuits and serve with a salad!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, French onion dip and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Spread out in a dish.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 1 package taco seasoning and water.
Simmer and cool.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: baked ham with peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Baking schedule: 15 minutes per pound.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl.
Slice French bread lengthwise.
Butter lightly.
Spread thickly with cheese mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and crust is slightly crunchy.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Slice into thick pieces.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, salt and onion together, then mix with potatoes.
Mix cheese with the mixture and put in baking dish.
Crush corn flakes; mix with butter.
Mix good and cover top of potato casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza bread dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and let stand.
Put sugar, salt and oil in large bowl.
Stir in dissolved yeast.
Add flour and water alternately.
Turn on a lightly floured board and knead gently.
Divide dough into 2 sections.
Brush tops with olive oil. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream all ingredients but sugar. Add sugar a little at a time to taste.
Mix well.
Shape into eggs and chill well.
Melt 1 pound of chocolate and dip eggs.

title: sister lester's chicken and dumplings
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to water of cooking hen.
Cook until meat falls off bone; let cool.
Take chicken off bone.
Take out 2 cups of broth for mixing dumplings.

title: sour cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and butter.
Press firmly in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Beat in eggs, then sour cream and last vanilla. Pour into pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Center will be slightly soft.
Cool, chill and top with cherry pie filling.

title: deer hunter's spaghetti
directions: Brown meats, drain off grease.
In a large pan combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat 3-4 hours.
Stir occasionally. Pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped corn in roaster pan.
Combine sugar, butter, syrup, salt and molasses in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry sauce
directions: Hull berries and gently rinse; pat dry.
Puree one cup of the blueberries in your blender.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water to make smooth mixture, then stir in the pureed berries and the remaining cup of whole berries. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice.
Great on French toast, pancakes, waffles or cheese blintzes!
Serves 4.

title: easy chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375F.
In Large Bowl mix 2/3 of frosting, Peanut Butter, egg and blend well.

title: potato skins
directions: Wash and bake potatoes in microwave.
When done, quarter potatoes.
Put them on a plate.
Cook pound of bacon.
Drain and crumble into small pieces.
Chop onions.
On the potatoes, squirt cheese on heavily.
Sprinkle bacon and cheese on top.
Add garlic and salt and pepper to taste.
Re-warm in microwave for 3 minutes if needed.
Top with sour cream, if desired.

title: oven barbecued brisket
directions: Trim away excess fat from brisket, pierce both sides of brisket with fork and sprinkle moderately with tenderizer.
Place in roasting pan large enough for meat to lay flat.
Blend together all the above ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake tightly closed at 300° for 4 1/2 to 5 1/2 hours until tender.
Slice in thin slices across the grain.
Great served with Potato salad, green beans or baked beans.

title: spicy apples
directions: Into a large wide saucepot, turn the water, sugar, orange juice, cloves and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until sugar is dissolved.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: dessert winter fruit bowl
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly drain fruits.
(Reserve fruit syrups for later use in beverage, gelatin salads, desert sauce or meat glaze.)

title: baked brunch
directions: Grease 11 x 7-inch casserole/pan.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, dry mustard and onion salt.
Crumble bacon or sausage into eggs and milk mixture.
Put croutons on bottom of casserole, then grated cheese.
Pour egg mixture over it.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Serves 2 to 4.

title: bread & butter pickles
directions: Chop cucumbers in thin slices. Chop onions and peppers into bite size pieces. Cover with the salt and let stand for about 3 hours. Drain well. Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large kettle and bring to boil. Add cucumbers and vegetables and heat thoroughly, but do not boil. Pack while hot loosely into sterilized canning jars. Do not crowd the pickle pieces. They are much more flavorful if the spices can get to them. Pour the hot juice over each to within 1/4 inch of top of jar and seal. Add a few 1 inch sticks of carrots and a few trees of cauliflower with the other vegetables if you would like.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs in evenly.
Add butterscotch and chocolate bits, coconut and nuts. Pour Eagle Brand milk over it.
Spread out evenly with a fork if you wish.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut in bars.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: best pear preserves
directions: Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; add onion. Microwave on High, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add beans, rice, catsup, 3 tablespoons brown sugar, mustard and pepper.
Mix well.
Cut apple into 10 thin slices.
Arrange in clockwise pattern on top of the casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon brown sugar.
Cover with lid.
Microwave at High for 8 to 9 minutes or until heated through (150°).
Serves 6.

title: mozzarella garlic bread
directions: Combine butter and garlic.
Preheat broiler.
Spread garlic butter on cut surfaces of bread.
Top with Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil until golden brown, about 3 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-up
directions: Mix all together.
Spread mix on one package large tortilla soft shells.
Roll, refrigerate and slice before serving.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, cook chicken (cut up), carrots, bay leaf, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water.
Simmer 35 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Remove all skin and fat.

title: coconut dip
directions: Mix sour cream, coconut cream (Coco Lopez) and brown sugar. Use dip for fruit sections.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: cranberry ring mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Take juice and add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add juice.
Cool slightly and then add all other ingredients.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (1/2 recipe makes an 8 x 8 dish).

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
Double recipe for larger quantity.

title: date filled refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add beaten eggs and beat again.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll dough out in a sheet 1/2-inch thick for filling.
Spread filling on dough and roll like jelly roll.
Chill.
Slice thin.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(It will be very thin.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until light brown).
Cool.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Use large bowl and whip together cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and pineapple juice.
Then fold in tidbits of cherries and pecans; chill.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper; set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, butter Crisco and mint extract.
Beat in confectioners sugar at low speed of electric mixer until mixture is stiff and crumbly.
Add food coloring to mixture (to make mints different colors, divide mixture and tint each part).
Shape by 1/2 teaspoons into balls.
Place on prepared baking sheet.
Using fork tines dipped in confectioners sugar, flatten each candy in crisscross pattern to 1/2-inch thick.
Or, if desired, shape, using mint molds.
Let stand overnight to dry.
Makes 8 to 9 dozen candies.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust.
Spread lemon pudding on top.
Top with the Cool Whip and chopped nuts. (I used toasted almonds and coconut on top.)

title: sausages and mustard sauce
directions: Brown sausages and drain.
Heat mustard and jelly in double boiler until dissolved and heated.
Cut sausages in bite-size pieces and serve in chafing dish.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions in margarine until tender.
Add bouillon, pepper, water and Worcestershire.
Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes to blend flavors.
To serve, top each serving with a slice of bread and sliced cheese.
If desired, place under broiler or bake until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. White wine can replace 1 cup of water for a rich flavor.

title: norma's basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add a dash of sugar. Meanwhile in large bowl, combine flour, salt and oil.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Add yeast and mix thoroughly, adding warm water as needed until the mixture becomes sticky.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Separate dough in oiled pans patting and stretching with hands (you need to put oil on dough too to help you work with it without sticking too much to hands).
Once you get the hang of it, it's not as complicated as it sounds!
Give it a try!

title: turkey divan
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish. Cook broccoli as directed on package until almost done (crisp-tender); drain.
Arrange broccoli in prepared baking dish. Lay turkey on top.

title: winter squash casserole
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and place in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Top with sunflower or sesame seed.
Place casserole dish in a pan with about 2 inches of water.
Bake in the oven at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes or until firm in the center.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cocuzza with eggs
directions: Put Cocuzza, tomato sauce,
water,
onion and garlic in pot; season to taste.
When
Cocuzza
is tender, break eggs in pot and cook until set.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole.
Sprinkle the potato chips on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no crust cheese cake
directions: Butter a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Mix eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Pour into pie plate and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and cool for 20 minutes.
Top with mixture of sour cream, 3 teaspoons sugar and vanilla.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove, cool and store in refrigerator.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: chocolate chip cake with brown sugar topping
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in medium bowl.
Beat margarine and shortening in large bowl on medium speed, about 30 seconds.
Beat in sugars and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beat on medium speed for 1 minute after each addition. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately to sugar mixture.
Beat on low speed after each addition.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.
Frost with Brown Sugar Topping.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: In a large pan, brown onion and ground beef in oil.
Add all other ingredients except cheeses and lasagna.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally about 30 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: May add chopped ham or bacon

title: escarole and beans
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil; add sausage.
After sausage is browned, add escarole.
Tear or cut in small pieces.
Add beans and white wine (peppers if desired).
Add water and chicken bouillon to taste.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: lemon-pecan cookie brittle
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat butter in mixer bowl until smooth. Beat in 1 cup confectioners sugar until fluffy.
Beat in lemon peel and salt.
Beat in flour until well combined.
Stir in pecans. (Mixture will be crumbly.)
With lightly floured fingertips, press dough into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan, leaving edges slightly thicker.
Bake 25 to 28 minutes, until top is completely golden.
Transfer to wire rack to cool.
Sift remaining 1 tablespoon confectioners sugar on top.
Break into chunks as desired.
Makes 50 (2 x 1 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: microwave baked custard
directions: Place milk in 2-cup glass measure.
Heat in microwave on full power for 3 to 4 minutes or until hot.
Stir sugar and salt into eggs.
Blend well.
Gradually stir in hot milk and vanilla, stirring constantly.

title: strawberry bavarian cream
directions: Drain strawberries; reserve syrup.
Pour boiling water over Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Add enough cold water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Stir into Jell-O.
Chill until almost set.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Beat Jell-O until foamy.
Fold Jell-O and strawberries into whipped cream.
Pour into mold.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy, easy biscuits
directions: Mix together and bake until firm and brown (350°).
Bake in muffin tins.
Makes 12 muffins. These are great in the morning with jelly or jam.
The margarine is already in the biscuit!

title: hollyberry punch
directions: Combine juices, water and grenadine.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour over ice in bowl.
Float slices of lime, lemon or orange.
Sherbet may be added.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add spices, grated onion and about 1 tablespoon of sour cream or mayonnaise.
Mix with a fork.
May be refrigerated for about an hour.

title: orange breeze dump salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, jello, orange slices and pineapple and mix well.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Wash bulghur.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Add all chopped vegetables and mix well.
Add oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Allow bulghur to soak and absorb the juice (about 1 hour). Serve over fresh green lettuce.
Eat with lettuce leaves, tender grape leaves or with a fork.
Makes a refreshing appetizer or a picnic salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Combine butterscotch chips, corn syrup, water and oil. Microwave until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Transfer to large bowl, add noodles and mix well.
Cool slightly.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on waxed paper. Chill 20 minutes.
Eat!

title: almond crust cherry cream pie
directions: Add nuts to pie shell. If using prepared fruit, mix in; bake. Combine condensed milk, lemon juice, vanilla and almond extract. Stir until thickened. Fold in whipped cream (or Cool Whip) into cooled shell. Top with cherry pie filling. Chill 2-3 hours.

title: how to boil water without burning a pan
directions: Fill medium saucepan or kettle with water.
Place on the stove on high temperature.
Set timer for 7 minutes.
Remove from stove when the timer rings.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Mix ingredients and beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Put in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter sandwich with sugar
directions: On 1 slice of bread, spread peanut butter, then sprinkle sugar on top.
Top with other slice of bread and enjoy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix with melted margarine and 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour half the batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
While batter bakes, melt caramels with remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour caramel mixture over top and sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Add remaining half of batter.
Return to oven and bake for 20 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Sift together the salt, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Add rolled oats, raisins and nuts.
Combine all ingredients and drop 1/2 teaspoon for each cookie on cookie sheet, ungreased.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on board before storing.
Will make several dozen.

title: spiced percolator punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and salt in a 30-cup percolator.
Place cloves, cinnamon stick and orange peel in the basket of the percolator.
Heat until hot.
Makes 20 (6 ounce) servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add eggs. Mix food color and cocoa into a paste. Add to creamed mixture. Add vanilla. Sift flour and salt together; add alternately with buttermilk. Mix vinegar and soda together and fold into mixture. Bake at 350 degrees 25-30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour pineapple into large bowl.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over pineapple and stir well.
Add pecans.
Let pudding mixture set for about 5 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Cut eggplant in slices 1/2-inch thick and lay in salt water for 1 hour.
Drain and dip in beaten egg, then in cornmeal, cracker crumbs or flour.
Fry until brown and nicely tender.
They are good fried after ham.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen ingredients, thin soup and pour over buttered cracker crumbs for topping.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole dish, combine green pepper, tomato, onion and butter.
Cook, covered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring once.
Stir in cooked rice, water, salt and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture is heated through, stirring once. Makes 6 side-dish servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meats; cook onions and celery in water.
Add browned meat.
Add bean sprouts, vegetables and mushrooms.
Simmer to blend flavor.
This is your liquid or broth.
Make a paste of the cornstarch and add to broth to make it thick like gravy.
Season with the soy sauce and bead molasses to make the brown color you like.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Cut cheeses into small cubes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift
flour and soda.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, one
at
a	time.
Beat
well.
Add flour and sour cream alternately
to batter.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt stick of margarine.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and mix well.
Add powdered sugar, beginning with 1/2 cup until mixture can be picked up (not quite as thick as pie pastry).
Press into a buttered dish.
Cool, cut and eat!

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Heat milk, marshmallows and chopped candy in a double boiler. When cool, fold in whipping cream, which has been whipped.
Pour into a cooled baked pie shell.
Chill before serving.

title: easy cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into a greased pie plate or 8X8 inch pan. Combine remaining ingredients, and mix with a fork. Crumble mixture over pie filling. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes, or microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes, or until hot.

title: stir-fried chicken and vegetables
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips.
Heat oil in frypan.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken turns white.
Add soy sauce and stir.
Add celery, mushrooms and stir-fry vegetables.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add slowly to chicken mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until ingredients are coated with a thin glaze, about 1 minute.
Serve with hot rice and extra soy sauce.

title: sirloin strip stroganoff
directions: Cook steak strips in 1/4 cup margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until light brown.
Sprinkle steak with salt, thyme and pepper.
Stir in mushrooms, onion and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until steak is tender, about 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Mix soup and milk; stir into steak mixture.
Heat until soup is hot.
Drain noodles; toss with 1 tablespoon butter and poppy seed.
Serve Stroganoff over noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: down home barbecue sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat all ingredients to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Simmer 10 minutes. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, Crisco and eggs.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape into balls.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and roll balls into mixture to coat.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: angel crisp cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip top in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down in center with finger. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: super nacho
directions: Saute beef, sausage and onions until beef is browned.
Drain fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread refried beans in casserole and top with meat mixture.
Add chopped green chilies. Cover evenly with grated cheese.
Spread taco sauce over this mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with green onion, olives, avocado dip and sour cream.
Use tortilla chips around edge and serve.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets. Chop tender stalks. Saut bacon until crisp; break up and set aside. Slice onion lengthwise, then cut into julienne strips. In a large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust:
Cut butter into flour and mix well.
Blend in chopped nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake approximately 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool crust.

title: brunch pie
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Combine hash with one beaten egg and press into pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Saute onion in margarine. Layer cheese, onion and vegetables in the crust.
Beat together remaining ingredients.
Pour over cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until filling is set and golden.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: orange coconut balls
directions: Crush wafers, add butter and thawed orange juice.
Mix well. Add confectioners sugar and as many pecans as desired.
Roll into balls and roll in fresh coconut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, catsup and lemon juice. Blend until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields about 4 cups.

title: turkey supper pies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook frozen broccoli and drain, pressing out as much water as possible. Cool to room temperature. Beat egg yolk with sour cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper. Stir in cheese, turkey and broccoli.
Refrigerate until cold. Follow general directions for preparing and baking puff pastry. Divide mixture among 8 pastry squares.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: five layer dip
directions: Add 2 layers of the refried beans, avocado dip, sour cream and salsa over the chips (in order).
Top with shredded sharp cheese.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease pie pan generously.
Make the Bisquick as you would for regular biscuits.
Fry hamburger and then add onions (drain all extra grease), then add pepperoni, mushrooms and spaghetti sauce.
Dish in the pie pan after you have already made your crust from the Bisquick, then add the Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes or until your crust is a light brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may add chopped almonds or water chestnuts for variations.

title: noah(cabbage salad)
directions: Combine cabbage and apple in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and sour cream, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Add to cabbage mixture and toss lightly.
Correct seasonings.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh peach parfait pie
directions: Toast oatmeal in shallow pan for 5 minutes at 350°.
Add almonds and toast for 5 more minutes.
Combine with sugar and butter.
Reserve some of the crumbs for the top of pie.
Press in pie pan and chill.
Dissolve orange jello in the boiling water; add vanilla ice cream and the peaches.
Pour in the pie shell and sprinkle the crumbs around edge and on top.
Chill several hours.

title: chicken shish kabob
directions: Combine pineapple juice, soy sauce and oil in a baking dish and marinate chicken in the mixture for 3 hours.
Alternate chicken with tomatoes, green peppers, onions and mushrooms on skewers.
Broil for 10 to 15 minutes, turning once, or until chicken is cooked through.
To barbecue, cook 5 inches from flame using marinade to baste.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: mandarin ice
directions: Heat water and 1 cup mandarin juice with sugar and salt until sugar dissolves.
Chill completely.
Combine with remaining mandarin and lemon juice.
Pour into a pan and freeze firm. Serves 4.

title: spicy chicken chow mein(crock-pot recipe)
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken pieces and cook until brown. Drain and put in slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients, except the cornstarch and water. Stir to combine. Cover and cook on low 6-8 hours.

title: rocky road fudge bars
directions: Immediately pour over marshmallows and swirl together.

title: rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon, cabbage and potatoes
directions: Cut bacon in small bits and fry until crisp.
Chop cabbage and potatoes and add to bacon and grease.
Mix and cook until done.

title: "holiness" rolls(crescent rolls)
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, eggs and water.
Add oil, salt and flour. Let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Divide into 3 parts; roll out as if you were making pie crust.
Cut into 8 sections the shape of pieces of pie.
Roll wide edge into the point (like crescent rolls) and place on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 6 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour; gradually stir in broth.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil; boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in rice and salt; simmer about 5 minutes.
Blend in half and half and sherry; heat to serving temperature.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: In a separate bowl, pour the boiling water over the oatmeal. Mix the brown sugar, granulated sugar, butter or margarine and eggs and cream together.
Beat in the vanilla, oatmeal mixture, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, mace (optional) and salt. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in it about 1-inch apart using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour sweetened condensed milk and caramel topping over cake, making sure cake is completely covered.
Refrigerate overnight.
When serving, garnish with whipped topping and sprinkle with Heath bar crumbs.

title: lo mein
directions: *Whatever you like:
Carrots, celery, scallions, green peppers, cabbage, mushrooms, peas, green beans, onions, zucchini, etc.

title: deer jerky
directions: Bake in oven at 200° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or to taste.

title: congo squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Spread mixture into 9 x 12-inch pan (lightly greased).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
Mitchell Family favorite.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Cool slightly.
Slice 2 bananas and dip in lemon juice; drain. Arrange bananas on the bottom of the crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Cover and chill 4 hours or until set.
Spread top with Cool Whip.
Slice remaining banana and dip in lemon juice, then arrange on top of pie.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add vanilla.
Mix well. Combine salt, flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk.
Drop onto ungreased baking sheets.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 400° for approximately 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit delight
directions: Put pudding, Tang and 1 cup of reserved juices (a little at a time) in a blender.
Pour over pineapple chunks and oranges. Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add salt, Karo and margarine and beat well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 pie.

title: baked cheese and crab dip
directions: Mix crab meat, Swiss cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and onions together; bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: dressing
directions: Saute in butter the onion, celery and mushrooms (optional). Mix everything together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Mix well, then blend in blender.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and cook at 350° until firm.

title: chocolate zucchini bars
directions: *To make sour milk or buttermilk, add 1/2 tablespoon vinegar or lemon juice to milk to equal 1/2 cup.
Allow souring milk to rest a few minutes.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm and add frozen orange juice, stirring to melt.
Chill until slightly syrupy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into serving bowl and chill.

title: mr. dave's fudge brownie pie
directions: Grease a pie plate.
In a saucepan, melt the cocoa, sugar and butter over low heat and stir until smooth.
Add the eggs, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Pour the mixture into the prepared pie plate.
Put the pie in a cold oven.
Set the oven at 325° and bake for 25 minutes.
Top with ice cream and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: side dish carrots for barbecue
directions: Peel carrots and slice in rounds.
Cook until tender, but still crunchy; set aside.
Simmer remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Mix carrots with 1 small, chopped onion and 1 small, chopped green pepper.
Add sauce; mix all and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.
Will keep for 1 to 2 weeks, covered.

title: layered ranchero dip
directions: On serving platter, spread bean dip; in small bowl, combine sour cream, mayo or cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean dip.
Peel, pit and mash avocados; combine with lime juice, salt and garlic.
Spread over sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese, onions, tomatoes, lettuce and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli.
Layer chicken and broccoli
in greased
baking
dish.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and pour
over chicken
and
broccoli.
Cover with crumb mixture, bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Serves about 12.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Cook on low heat 8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: easy tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Combine cream of mushroom soup, milk, mayonnaise and cheese packet from macaroni and cheese dinner.
Blend until smooth.
Add cooked macaroni, drained tuna and soup mixture.
Stir until mixed.
Turn into 2-quart casserole sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: matt's favorite orange bran muffins
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in large bowl.
Make well in center of mixture; set aside.
Combine wheat bran and boiling water in a large bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Place eggs, buttermilk and chopped orange in a container of an electric blender or a food processor; process until smooth.
Add buttermilk mixture to bran mixture; stir well.
Add sugar, butter and oil.
Stir well and add to bran mixture.
Add buttermilk mixture/bran mixture.
Add dried fruit; stir and mix into flour.
Stir until all dry ingredients are moist.
Cover batter and store in refrigerator up to 1 month.

title: cheesecake glazes(take your choice, you can't go wrong!)
directions: Several hours before serving, wash, hull and thoroughly dry strawberries.
In saucepan, combine several tablespoons jelly with cornstarch, mix well.
Add remaining jelly, Cointreau and water. Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until thickened and clear, about 5 minutes.
Cool to lukewarm, stirring occasionally. Serves 10 to 15.

title: california artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients well using a spoon or spatula. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with lightly toasted French or Italian bread.

title: chicken wings
directions: Marinate wings in a mixture of corn oil, soy sauce and ginger for 3 hours; discard marinade.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Divide pastry into 2 parts.
Line a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan with 1 part of the pastry.
Melt butter; add flour and seasonings.
Let bubble.
Add liquid and cook slowly until thickened.
Add chicken; pour into pan.
Top with rest of pastry. Bake 35 minutes.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown the beef and onion and add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
You may add 1 teaspoon of salt.

title: fruit drink
directions: Blend fruit, ice and powdered milk in blender until thick. Add ice to desired thickness.
Add sweetener to taste.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Mix broth and chicken or celery soup together. Pour over deboned chicken.
Pour 1 can drained peas and carrots over.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: vegetable rice
directions: In a small saucepan, combine chicken broth, carrot, celery, onion, margarine, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add rice.
Cover; let stand 5 to 8 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Garnish with cashews and parsley.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together egg yolks, condensed milk, sugar, flour and evaporated milk.
Cook at medium heat until thick, then pour over sliced bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: egg casserole
directions: Put bread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cook sausage, then crumble and drain.
Put on top of bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and salt together and put on top of bread and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best when made several hours or a day ahead before use.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: pasta spinach salad(low-fat)
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, then drain.
In a bowl, combine pasta, tomatoes, cheese, salad dressing, green onion and olives.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill.
Arrange spinach on a serving platter; spoon on pasta.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Add enough water to make a slightly stiff, rollable dough.
Roll out as thin as possible.
Cut into strips.
Drop into a rich boiling chicken broth.
Simmer on low 45 minutes to an hour.
Chicken may be left in the broth.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot oiled skillet.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: fulton mansion sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins, together and cook slowly until thick.
Add the raisins and stir the mixture occasionally until it's cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerettes into very small pieces.
