Cook and crumble bacon into small pieces.
Chop onion into small long pieces.
Mix these ingredients in large bowl.
Add grated cheese. Mix in small bowl, the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and chill well.
Serves 6.

title: chinese meat balls
directions: Preheat frypan at 300°.
Put cabbage and onion through meat grinder, using coarse cutter.
Combine ginger, salt and soy sauce. Add to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into balls about 1 to 1 1/2-inches.
Fry in oil or shortening until done, browning well on all sides.

title: crock-pot potato dish
directions: Season raw potatoes.
Put potatoes, bacon strips, onion and butter in crock-pot on low overnight.
Remove from crock-pot to pan.
Cover with cheese (it will melt from heat of potatoes). Serve with a main dish.

title: broasted chicken
directions: Heat and blend thoroughly.
Dip chicken in flour, then in sauce.
Place in pan.
Pour remainder of sauce over meat.
Cover and bake in 450° oven 15 minutes.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done in a 325° oven.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat until hot margarine and milk. Pour into this eggs, cornstarch, sugar and vanilla. Pour into pie shell. Cook at 300° until brown on top (about 1 hour).

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Blend in shortening.
Add sour milk and work lightly.
Bake in well-greased pan.
Bake in hot oven.

title: beet salad
directions: Bring water and bouillon granules to boil; continue boiling until granules are dissolved. Remove from heat and dissolve Jell-O, stirring constantly 2 minutes. Place beets with juice in blender and use the "chop" cycle. Mix all ingredients and add to Jell-O. Chill until set.

title: praline confections
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil.
(Note: Sheet should have a "lip".
A 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan is a good size.)
Arrange graham crackers over foil.

title: cream cheese olive spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Keeps very well.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Spread pie mix in greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over. Dribble melted butter over.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle coconut over and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and oil in the water.
Cook on stove top at medium heat until a mashed potato consistency. Add the food coloring of your choice.
Keep fresh in airtight containers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add oleo to rice. Stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Put in greased, 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: praline crackers
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and nuts.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes, while stirring.
Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for at least 10 minutes.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers, sugar and vinegar in a pan. Cook on high heat; stir until it comes to a hard boil. Boil 1 minute. Stir constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in Certo. Let sit 5 minutes. Skim off foam with metal spoon. Pour quickly into jelly glasses. Seal with lids while jelly is still real hot.

title: meltaways
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, butter, sugar, maple and salt at low speed; increase to medium.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Drop dough by teaspoons about 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Gently press pecan half into top of cookie.
Bake 12 minutes until browned.

title: best ever sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and dry.
Pack in jars.
Mix and pour over cucumbers cold.
Seal with a hot lid.

title: mrs. holy's cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan and bring to boil, let boil 1 minute.
Take off heat. Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, raisins, onion, carrots, sunflower seed, vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve cold.
Sprinkle bacon on top before serving.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes. While still hot, poke holes in cake with fork in layers.
Pour icing over cake.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef and cheese dip
directions: Combine cooking wine and onion flakes and set aside for 1 hour.
Whip cream cheese and mayonnaise until mixed well and slightly fluffy.
Add cut up dried beef, olives and onions.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients on plate in order given.
Serve with taco or corn chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn and eggs.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt, mustard and onion.
Stir in milk and butter.
Bake in a 3-quart greased baking dish for 1 hour in 400° oven, stirring once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Barely cook broccoli until tender.
Mix all other ingredients and place in casserole.
Add drained broccoli and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good kept in refrigerator for 2 days before serving.

title: meat loaf (tip)
directions: Make favorite meat loaf recipe.
In loaf pan, layer 2 inches meat mixture.
Peel eggshells, layer eggs in center.
Top meat mixture and pack firm.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour.
Half an hour before removing from oven, add tomatoes and peas.
Heat until warm.

title: cinnamon apple mince muffins
directions: Cook 400° oven.
Grease 18 muffin cups or line with paper baking cups.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes.
Blend all ingredients well.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Stir with wooden spoon.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes. Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened. Serve over noodles, potatoes, etc.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Form into meatballs and brown. Saute for 5 minutes the celery, onion and pepper.
Add beef consomme.
Add meatballs and serve over rice.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies with peanut butter
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil for a few minutes.
Stir to avoid burning. Add the oatmeal, nuts and peanut butter. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Chop all ingredients, try to keep the juices.
Mix all ingredients together.
Make at least 3 to 5 days ahead.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown the chicken (do not cook).
Place chicken in a large casserole dish.
Layer vegetables on top of chicken.
Mix soup, sour cream and water.
As you layer chicken and vegetables, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and vegetables.
Cover and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg with milk; stir in the 1 tablespoon melted Crisco and the fruit.
Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture and stir just until mixed.
Drop from tablespoon into deep Crisco heated to 375°.
Fry about 4 minutes, until brown and done in the center. Drain on paper toweling.
Serve hot.
If desired, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 16.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in a small amount of salted water until tender.
Mix
melted
margarine
in
stuffing mix with a little water.
Layer
stuffing
mix
(save
a small amount for topping), squash
and
onions,
pouring soup over them.
Layer cheese slices and top with balance of stuffing mix.

title: no egg chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs singly.
Mix in vanilla wafers, milk, coconut and pecans thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured 1-inch tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool in pan.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Fold in cocoa and oats.
Drop from tablespoon onto wax paper; let cool.
(No baking necessary.)

title: cheesy corn chowder
directions: Cover potatoes with water. Add salt and onion; bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender. Drain. Add milk and heat through. Stir in remaining ingredients and heat on low until cheese is melted. Serve hot. Yields 12 to 14 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti following label directions. Drain.

Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg until thoroughly combined. Spread mixture evenly in pan. Saute the ground chuck, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until meat is brown.
Drain. Stir in spaghetti sauce, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti layer. Top with meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain off juices.
Mix ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: ritch's sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and vanilla pudding together.
Add sour cream and 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Line the bottom of a bowl with a layer of wafers.
Slice 2 to 3 bananas and place on top of wafers. Cover with pudding mixture.
Put a second layer of wafers on pudding mixture.
Top with a second layer of bananas.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and Jell-O; add remaining ingredients.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring to boil first 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Add flour.
Stir in eggs 1 at a time.
Put in greased muffin pan. (Makes 8.)
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes.
Fill with cream pudding.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl.
Pack into 2 tube pans or loaf pans.
Refrigerate overnight.
This is great to put in mini loaf pans and give to friends at Christmas.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Keep in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: coffee walnut chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12 (3-inch) muffin tins.

Cream together the butter, sugars, coffee and vanilla. Beat together eggs and milk. Combine flour, salt and baking powder. Alternately add wet and dry ingredients to butter mixture. Stir just to combine.
Add chips and nuts by hand. Fill muffin tins. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in tins, then remove and continue cooling on racks.

title: grilled italian sausage and peppers
directions: Fold a 36-inch piece of heavy foil in half to make a grilling tray.
Cut peppers into julienne strips.
Place peppers and sliced onion in the center of the tray; drizzle with salad dressing. Fold and seal foil.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Put graham cracker crust in bottom of ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan, following cheese cake directions.
Mix filling from cheese cake according to directions.
Mix in pineapple.
Spread over crust.
Layer of fruit cocktail.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut. Spread over top.
Refrigerate.
For 9 x 13-inch pan, use 2 packages of Jell-O cheese cake and large cans of pineapple and fruit cocktail.

title: bean bake
directions: Add all the beans to the hamburger, bacon and onion. Add the vinegar, brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and sugar. Mix and simmer 45 minutes on low.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients 3 minutes. Pour into one 10-inch pie pan and let stand 5 minutes. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.
(The Bisquick will make a crust.)

title: simple fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in loaf pan.
Stir in cake mix (one layer size). Add fruit mix to top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Crust will rise to top while cooking.

title: tofu-cheese-stuffed shells(yields 4 servings)
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain. Rinse with cold water.
Set aside.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, cook carrot and green onion in small amount of water until tender.
Drain.

title: polish sausage and cheese potatoes
directions: Slice sausages and potatoes.
Mix together, then add cheese and butter.
Microwave or cook in oven.
Stir as it cooks to mix well.

title: barbecue baked fish
directions: In 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish place fish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Top with lemon, onion and parsley. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour soup over, stirring into liquid around fish.
Bake 10 minutes more or until done.
Stir before serving.
Makes 3 servings.

title: deer or beef jerky
directions: Cut the venison into thin strips no more than 1/4-inch. Combine soy sauce and seasonings.
Pour over strips in a large bowl.
Mix well and marinate for 8 to 10 hours.
Place the strips on a wire rack over a baking sheet.
Allow the strips to touch, but not overlap.
Bake in the oven on low (150° to 170°) for 10 to 12 hours.
(Let this bake during the night.)
Thicker pieces may need to take longer.
When cool store in Ziploc bags at room temperature.

title: rich cheese puffs
directions: In large bowl, blend butter and cream cheese.
Beat in eggs and hot sauce until light and fluffy.
Blend in cheese.
Stir in flour and salt.
Chill 30 minutes.
On generously floured board, roll half of dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 1 3/4 to 2-inch cookie cutter.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place puffs close together on 3 ungreased baking sheets.

title: choice moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a bowl.
Add vanilla, vinegar and oil.
Pour water over all.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch sheet pan and bake at 350°.
Cake will be moist.

title: tomatoes and mozzarella with basil vinaigrette
directions: Whisk oil, vinegar, basil, mustard, salt and pepper in non-metal bowl.
Alternately arrange tomatoes and cheese in non-metal casserole dish.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown at 350°.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: chicken breasts teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour (overnight is better).
Remove chicken and reserve marinade.
Cover and grill chicken 5 to 6 inches from medium coals until golden brown, about 15 minutes; turn chicken.
Cover and grill, turning and brushing 2 or 3 times with marinade until chicken is done, 10 to 20 minutes longer. (Can also be used for beef or fish.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Cut strawberries into small pieces; cover with glaze.
Mix powdered sugar, sour cream, evaporated milk and Cool Whip.
Break angel food cake into small pieces.
Stir into mixture.
Layer cake mixture in bottom of bowl and then a layer of the strawberry mixture.
Chill for at least 6 to 8 hours.

title: shrimp stuffed roll-ups
directions: Bring water to a boil; add shrimp and return to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Rinse shrimp in cold water; peel and devein.
Chop 8 shrimp.
Set aside. Reserve remaining shrimp for garnish.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until onion is tender.
Add chopped shrimp, breadcrumbs, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well and remove from heat.
Divide shrimp mixture evenly to spread over fillets.
Roll up each fillet and secure with a wooden pick.
Pour half of remaining butter into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange fillets in baking dish; brush with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove fillets to serving dish.
Top with Blender Hollandaise Sauce and garnish with remaining shrimp.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except bacon.
Pour batter over bacon in hot
8-inch Dutch oven.	Use 1/2 bacon slice for each cake. Turn over when bubbles start to break.

title: blueberry gingerbread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg and beat.
Sift and measure flour.
Add ginger, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add milk and molasses alternately with the flour.
Add blueberries.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 3 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apricot peach jello salad
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine; press in a dish and chill 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, milk and Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs and chill; seal edges.
Place sliced peaches over cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: mother's mexican corn casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix together macaroni, corn, margarine, onions, tomatoes, salt, pepper and cheese.

title: cajun dressing
directions: Combine eggplant, water and 1 teaspoon salt in medium saucepan.

Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes; drain. Cook celery, onions and bell pepper in butter until tender-crisp. Stir in eggplant, rice, crawfish tails, crumbs, parsley, garlic powder, black pepper, red pepper and 2 teaspoons salt.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix chunk pineapple, mixed fruit or fruit cocktail, bananas, peeled apple (cut in small pieces) and mandarin oranges. Add cherries.
I grind mine up with the juice to add color and add 1 deal Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: To Make Meatballs: Combine meat, bread crumbs, onion, Worcestershire sauce, milk, salt and egg.
Mix well.
Shape into 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning often, until browned.
(May also bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.) Drain well.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Grease electric frying pan with margarine.
Brown meat; spread over pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Add 1/2 package dry spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Top with noodles.
Break up tomatoes; pour over noodles.
Add tomato sauce and the rest of dry spaghetti sauce.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Let cook on low at 150° to 200° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Heat ingredients in saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Serve warm.
Use as dip for chips and serve with cold Coronas or frozen margaritas.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Saute garlic in melted butter in small skillet over medium heat for 1 minute.
Set aside.

title: fruit crisp dessert
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sliced apples in greased 9-inch square pan or baking dish.
Blend remaining ingredients until mixture is crumbly.
Spread over apples.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in 8-inch iron skillet in 350° oven.
Coat pan with margarine.
Mix all ingredients until blended.
Pour remaining margarine into batter and mix well.
Pour batter into hot pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Do not use beater, just mix.
You may add any of the following:
1/2 cup diced apples, raisins, candied fruit and top with slivered almonds or walnuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased (sticks: use flour first) and sugared loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Check after 35 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before removing.
The bread freezes beautifully.
It is so good you may want to keep one of the starters for yourself.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown pork chops in oleo, salt and pepper. Place a thick slice of onion on each chop; pour tomatoes around the chops, about 1-inch in depth.
Add rice around in the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Cover tightly and simmer at 350° until chops are tender and rice is done.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until soft ball forms in cold water.
Take off stove.
Add peanut butter and marshmallow cream; keep stirring.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased pan or platter to cool.
Cut into squares.

title: back bay cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Sift remaining ingredients together and add to butter and sugar mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon 1 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: In skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender. Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese; stir into vegetable mixture.
Separate dinner roll dough into 8 triangles and place in 10 x 8-inch baking dish, pressing dough over bottom and sides to form a crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
If crust becomes too brown, cover with foil during last 10 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve hot.

title: doughnuts
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of flour and the yeast. In saucepan, heat together milk, sugar, shortening and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly to melt shortening. Add to dry mixture in mixer bowl; add eggs.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (5 to 8 minutes).
Shape into ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise in warm place until dough doubles (45 to 60 minutes).
Punch down; turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Divide in half.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter (has hole in center) into doughnuts.
Cover and let rise in warm place until very light (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Fry in deep hot fat (375°) until golden, about 1 minute on each side.
Drain on paper toweling.
If desired, roll warm doughnuts in sugar or frost with glaze.
Makes 18 to 20.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Heat oil with garlic in large pan over medium heat.
Dredge veal in flour.
When oil is hot, add the meat, mushrooms and onions.
Brown, stirring frequently.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Blend in herbs, spices and carrots.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, pouring in extra water as needed to keep meat covered.

title: italian vegetables
directions: *Can use broccoli, carrot slices, cauliflower, mushrooms, green and/or red bell peppers, yellow and/or zucchini strips or slices.

title: sub sandwiches
directions: Toss lettuce with 1/4 cup dressing.
Brush inside of bread with 1/4 cup dressing.
Layer bread with turkey, chicken, cheese, tomatoes and lettuce.
Make sure ingredients are spread evenly into loaf.
Microwave loaves or heat in oven at 400°, just until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except honey, in a bowl.
Pour into greased round skillet or Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 325° for approximately 35 minutes.
Serve with honey.

title: barbara's cornwallis yams
directions: Wash sweet potatoes and place in large sauce pan.
Cover with water and bring to boil, cover pan and simmer about 30 minutes until tender.
Peel potatoes and mash.
Add next 8 ingredients, mixing well. Pour into a greased 13x9x2
baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut before serving. Serves a lot.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Crumble saltines and combine with softened butter.
Press onto the bottom of a glass baking dish (a square one is good).
Saute the onions (peeled and sliced) in 2 tablespoons butter until golden, but not brown.
Put the onion mixture on top of the saltine crust.
Spread the grated cheese over this mixture.
Mix the custard in a bowl (milk, eggs, salt and pepper). Pour over the top of the casserole and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Bake until golden.
Keeps well. Freezes well, too!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli and boil with salt.
Leave the head of broccoli to steam last.
Drain broccoli and add cream of mushroom soup, onion, 3/4 bag of shredded cheese and sour cream to taste.
Stir ingredients together well.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: wheat hearts pancakes
directions: Beat egg, then beat in remaining ingredients in order given, sifting the dry ingredients.
Grease griddle and when hot, add batter for pancakes.
Turn pancake as soon as puffed and full of bubbles and before bubbles break.
Makes 10 (4-inch) golden brown cakes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix.
Spread on large platter or plate.
Layer lettuce, tomato and cheese.
Serve with Tostitos, Doritos or nacho chips.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix soup, water, flour until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients in covered stew pan.
Simmer browned stew meat, vegetables and spices til vegetables are cooked.
Serve over noodles and with crunchy French bread.

title: southern style short ribs of beef
directions: Trim extra fat away from each rib.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Roll in flour.
Brown on all sides, on a slow fire, remove fat from pan, add water and cover.
Simmer on stove top or cook in a slow 325° oven until tender, about 2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Make onion gravy, if desired.
Serve with your favorite vegetable.

title: christmas jam
directions: Process cranberries in food processor until coarsely chopped. Combine cranberries, strawberries, and sugar

in pan. Bring to boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat, add pectin. Return to full rolling boil, boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and skim off foam with metal spoon. Quickly, pour into hot jars and cover at once. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes. Makes 7 half pints.

title: custard icing
directions: Cook milk and flour. Stir until thick.
Cool in refrigerator. Stir in sugar, oleo and vanilla. Whip until very creamy. Keep cold.

title: pumpkin pie(makes two 9-inch pies)
directions: Mix and bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes, until hot and bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour in a bowl.
Add shortening; mix well.
Beat together the egg, water and vinegar; add to flour mixture.
Mix until well moistened.
Chill at least 15 minutes before using.

title: baked strawberry marbled cheese cake
directions: In blender container. combine strawberries and cornstarch; blend until smooth.
In heavy saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Reserve 1/3 cup sauce; cool.
Chill remaining sauce.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese. Pour into a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Cover and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven. Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. Add cheese and bake until melted.

title: fresh salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Let stand at room temperature for up to 2 hours.
Cover and refrigerate for longer storage.
Let return to room temperature before serving.

title: bentley brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Line with wax paper and grease paper.

title: shrimp whip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except shrimp, in a large bowl.
Add shrimp and toss well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate to marinate at least 24 hours.

title: zucchini cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo in greased casserole dish. Dot with oleo pats. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add sour cream, flour, salt and soda; beat well.
Spread half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over mixture.
Cover with rest of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp and corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon; crumble and set aside; reserve bacon fat. Saute onions, celery, bell pepper, and carrots in bacon fat. Add bay leaf, potatoes, and water. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle flour over mixture; stir well. Add shrimp stock; bring to boil. Add corn, milk, shrimp, salt, pepper, and Tabasco sauce. Simmer over low heat for approximately 30 minutes.

title: ranchburgers(serves at least 40 people)
directions: Brown hamburger and onions; drain grease.
Add all spices; stir.
Add the rest of ingredients.
(Put the chili beans and sauce through the blender first, then add.)
Cook on low-medium for about 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Also makes great chili dogs. Great for a big get together!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter and cream cheese.
Blend in sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell, freeze.
Thaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda. Combine egg, grated orange peel, orange juice and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan at 350° for 60 minutes or until done.
Remove from pan; cool.
Store overnight.

title: almond delight
directions: Prepare pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture over crumb mixture.
Add remaining crumbs for topping.
Chill.

title: chicken nachos
directions: In saucepan, mix soup, salsa and chicken.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring occasionally.
Serve over chips.
Top with onions and olives.
Serves 6.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Layer ice cream sandwiches in bottom of 9x13 baking dish. Spread Cool Whip over sandwiches.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Place in freezer until frozen.

title: turkey chowder
directions: In large pot, saute
onion
and
celery in butter until celery is almost tender.
Add
potato soup, corn, turkey stock or chicken broth, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Stirring constantly,
bring to boil.
Reduce
heat;
add
turkey
and
parsley. Simmer 5 minutes or until turkey is heated.	Makes 8 servings.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix on low with hand mixer until smooth and creamy.

title: ketchup
directions: Quarter tomatoes; remove stems.
Cut pepper into strips. Slice onions.
Blend in blender until soft.
Pour in large pot. Add vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard, red pepper and spice wrapped in a spice cloth.
Simmer in a slow oven on 325° until shrinks in half.
Remove spice cloth.
Pour into hot jars.
Process 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.
Cook in oven approximately 7 more hours.

title: strawberry short cake
directions: Mix together and spread on top.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Prepare
pastry
shell;
set aside.
Heat oven to 350°. In a medium bowl, cream butter; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and
flour;
add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips
and nuts;
pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake for 45 to 50
minutes or until golden.
Cook for about 1 hour;
serve warm.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Fluff up water with egg white.
Cover pecans with fluff. Blend sugar, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Add sugar mixture to pecans, stir to coat pecans evenly.
Spread pecans on a cookie sheet with sides and bake at 300° for about 33 minutes, stirring after every 11 minutes.

title: mrs. c. h. elliott's mother's pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco together.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour a tablespoon at a time and beat well. Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: quick overnight salad(excellent!  a quick, easy favorite!)
directions: Combine pudding mixes with 3 cups water.
Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add dry gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add the pineapple and juice.
Cool for about 2 hours in the refrigerator.
Blend in whipped topping and pour into bowl or jello mold.
Chill overnight.

title: sea chowder
directions: In saucepan, brown salt pork; remove.
In drippings, cook celery and onion until tender.
Add salt pork and remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until fish is done.
Stir often.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: spinach pie parma
directions: Combine margarine and enough croutons to line 10-inch pie plate.
Combine 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and remaining ingredients. Spoon into crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/8 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy mushroom soup(6 cups)
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 30 seconds.
Stir in mushrooms and saute until they release juices.
Sprinkle on flour and blend. Cook 1 minute.
Add stock, milk and sherry.
Bring to boil and stir constantly.
Add bay leaf and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in cream cheese, lemon juice and Tabasco.
Stir until smooth and cream cheese is melted.
Season with salt.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, margarine and powdered sugar with fork. Press into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: eggnog custard
directions: Slowly heat eggnog to almost a simmer. Beat eggs to combine them well. Slowly pour hot eggnog into eggs while beating. Strain mixture.
Pour mixture into 4 to 6 buttered custard cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place custard cups in a pan of hot water. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in the custard comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef brisket
directions: Put brisket, fat side down, in pan.
Slice onions and garlic over brisket.
Mix together beer, chili sauce, brown sugar and ketchup.
Pour over brisket and bake 4 hours at 325°.
Cover last 2 hours.
Sauce can be made 3 days in advance.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples as for pie (or drain juice off pie filling).
Sweeten to taste with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix brown sugar, oleo, flour and oats.
Put on top of apples; press down. Bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Mix all together and bake covered for 30 minutes at 350°. Uncover and cook 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Heat undiluted soup to hot, bubbly stage.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water and stir into soup.
Add mayonnaise and blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into salad mold and chill until firm. Rich and delicious.
Serves 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Cut corn off; cut up peppers, onions and cabbage.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Pack in heated jars.
Seal.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Cover sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with pie crusts. Pour in sliced apples.
Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon and flour and sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle water over this.
Combine 1 cup sugar, flour and margarine.
Crumble over top of pie.
Place in large brown paper bag.
Seal airtight with staples or paper clips.
Bake 1 hour at 425°.
Do not let bag touch sides of oven.

title: broccoli and beef pizza
directions: Cook broccoli 6 to 8 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain; set aside.
In skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic until meat is no longer pink.
Drain off fat.
Stir in flour.
Add tomato sauce and oregano.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook about 1 minute.
Set aside.
Preheat a large baking sheet in 400° oven about 5 minutes.
Arrange pita bread on baking sheet.
Divide the mixture, broccoli and cheese onto the bread.
Bake about 5 more minutes, until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy beans and cheese
directions: Mash beans thoroughly.
Add seasonings.
Simmer over low heat for about 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Continue to heat until completely melted.
Serve on warmed tortillas with salsa.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
On lightly floured surface, roll to a 15 1/2 x 9-inch rectangle.
Cut into 3 strips each 3 inches wide. Divide sausage into thirds; roll each into "snake" the length of the pastry.
Place each roll along 1 edge of pastry strips.
Roll the pastry around the sausage.
Wet the edges with ice water and press to seal tightly.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 12 minutes at 400°.
Makes 60.

title: rhubarb butter crunch
directions: Mix and place in a buttered baking pan.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine potatoes, salt, butter and pineapple.
Place half mixture in buttered casserole.
Top with half the marshmallows. Add remaining potato mixture.
Top with pecans.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes and add rest of marshmallows.

title: captain's kitchen fried shrimp
directions: Clean shrimp, leaving tails on (this makes shrimp more moist). Run cold water over shrimp; drain.
Pour chilled cream in small bowl.
Dip shrimp in cream, then shake in paper bag containing bread mix.
As you bread shrimp, place on platter.
Chill at least 1 hour, then fry in hot oil.
Salt while they are hot.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat out on pizza pan. Bake at 325° for 15-20 minutes. Cool.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut.
Add onion, bell pepper, celery and pimientos to kraut.
Pour sugar over mixture.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before using.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: butter fruit cake
directions: Line 2 baking pans and grease.
Prepare fruit (cut as desired).
Use about 3/4 cup flour to coat fruit.
Decrease the flour in the batter by this amount.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add crushed pineapple.
Add spices and flour.
The coconut is mixed with the fruit.
Pour batter over fruit and mix well in large container.
Place in baking pan and bake in preheated oven. Bake at 225° for 3 1/2 hours.
Do not overbake.
Place a pan of water in the oven and keep water in container during the time the cake is baking.

title: hash browns and ham breakfast
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine sour cream, soup, ham, potatoes, onion and American cheese.
Combine corn flakes and butter; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake for another 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill overnight.
Roll into balls the size of a nickle and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass.
Dip glass in water for first cookie only, then dip in white granulated sugar for each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown at edges.
Batter may be kept in refrigerator for 2 weeks or more.
May be frozen to use later.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in butter.
Stir in raisins and caraway seed and add buttermilk. Knead until smooth.

title: green and white salad
directions: Cut vegetables in bite-size pieces.
Mix dressing ingredients together and then mix into the vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peppers with cream cheese
directions: Wash and dry peppers.
Cut off stem end of pepper, taking a little of the pepper with you.
Remove stem and finely chop the excess pepper.
Remove seeds from peppers; set aside.
Blend cream cheese and whipping cream until smooth.
Add Cheddar cheese and paprika and cayenne (optional); blend well.
Add parsley and the chopped peppers; mix well.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or in freezer for 20 minutes. Cut into thin slices and serve.

title: barbara's party mix
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: You will also need a paper bag.

title: frozen sweet pickles
directions: Put in large container and refrigerate; stir daily for four days.
Then freeze in bags or containers.
Containers are better.

title: sharon's baked beans
directions: Mix beans, molasses and sugar.
Place in large bowl.
Cut bacon slices in 2-inch pieces and place on top of beans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mary's cabbage casserole
directions: Line a three-quart casserole dish with corn flakes.
Put in cut cabbage.
Heat soup, margarine and mayonnaise until bubbly hot.
Pour over cabbage.
Add a layer of cheese; then cover with corn flakes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions and celery.
Pour over crumbs and add seasonings.
Toss well.
Add broth and beaten egg, mixing well.
Pack lightly in greased crock-pot set on High.
Cook on High 4 hours.
Stir mixture once or twice during cooking time. You can add mushrooms and giblets.

title: frozen kahlua cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar; add cocoa and egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in water and combine with coffee and 1/2 cup Kahlua.
Add to batter alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and fold in beaten egg whites.

title: cabbage dish
directions: Saute onion in Crisco.
Drain cabbage, add to onion and mix. Add hot water (about 1 cup) and bring to a boil.
Add sugar, vinegar and a small amount of salt and pepper.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer for about 45 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Add more salt and pepper to taste.
In Dutch oven over medium heat, heat bacon fat.
Add onions and cook until tender, 5 minutes. Drain clams.
Add enough water to clam liquid to make 2 cups.
Stir flour into onion mixture until blended.
Gradually stir in clam liquid, garlic and bay leaf and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Stir in potatoes, celery, parsley, salt and pepper. Cover; cook until potatoes and celery are tender.
Add clams, milk and margarine until heated, stirring often.

title: lady cabbage
directions: Saute onion in butter one or two minutes.
Add cabbage, water and salt. Cover.
Cook 10 minutes or until crispy tender.
Stir in milk.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and shortening.
Pour hot water over this; let cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on top; let stand 10 minutes, then add flour to make stiff dough.
Let stand until it is double in bulk.
Take out the amount you want to cook.
Roll out; put in pan.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Cook at 425° until done. Store the rest in refrigerator.
It will keep 4 or 5 days.

title: six week raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients well; make hole in center.
Add the eggs, cooking oil and buttermilk; stir and mix well.
Fill muffin tins about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Can bake small amount as needed.
Batter will keep 5 to 6 weeks in refrigerator.

title: tomato soup
directions: Chop celery, onions and peppers into large chunks.
Cook slowly with a little water until soft.
Add tomatoes, bay leaves, parsley and cloves.
Cook slowly until very soft, perhaps 1 1/2 hours or longer.
Strain through a food mill and put back into a kettle.
Add sugar and salt slowly, tasting as you go.
The amount of salt and sugar comes from the original recipe before we worried about sodium.
Freeze.
